    "contract": "Fixed Price",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "DTAC all 5 domains, DCB0129, NHS Pathways licence, UK GDPR Article 9, NHS DSP Toolkit, WCAG 2.1 AA, HRA research ethics, Cyber Essentials Plus",
    "challenge": "An NHS Integrated Urgent Care (IUC) provider operating NHS 111 services for a population of 1.8 million people (500,000 calls/year) needed to digitise their clinical assessment workflow — reducing call handling time, improving ICD-10 symptom coding, and providing clinicians with real-time NHS Pathways decision support integration. NHS Pathways licence (CDSS — Clinical Decision Support System), DTAC all 5 domains, DCB0129 (urgent care is highest patient safety risk), NHS SDS authentication, UK GDPR Article 9, and WCAG 2.1 AA were mandatory. Budget: £90,000.",
    "approach": "NHS Pathways Clinical Decision Support Integration: NHS Pathways: CDSS used by all NHS 111 services — structured clinical assessment algorithm (1,500+ pathways) determining care disposition (self-care, primary care, urgent treatment centre, A&amp;E, 999). NHS Pathways API: ClickMasters integrated the Pathways API (licenced from NHS England) — clinical assessment inputs (symptom description, patient demographics, clinical observations) → Pathways API → structured disposition output (care level, time to care, clinical advice). Pathways integration eliminates manual pathway navigation — clinician enters structured responses, Pathways engine calculates disposition. ICD-10 Symptom Auto-Coding: ICD-10 (International Classification of Diseases, 10th revision): NHS 111 calls must be coded for national statistics reporting. Auto-coding: call summary (structured text) → NLP model → ICD-10 code suggestion (top 3 suggestions with confidence scores). Clinician validation: clinician selects correct ICD-10 code from suggestions — no automated final coding without clinical sign-off. Model training: 42,000 anonymised NHS 111 call summaries (HRA ethics approval) → BioBERT fine-tuned for NHS 111 ICD-10 coding task. Coding accuracy: 88% top-1 match (clinician accepts first suggestion). DCB0129 Urgent Care Clinical Safety: Highest hazard: NHS Pathways API downtime during call causing delay to safety-netting. Mitigation: NHS Pathways API multi-region redundancy, local Pathways cache (last-known pathway state if API unavailable), and documented fallback protocol (paper pathway card available at every clinical workstation). Second hazard: ICD-10 auto-coding error causing incorrect statistics. Mitigation: ICD-10 coding is never patient-facing — statistics only — clinician always validates. Real-Time Capacity Integration: NHS Urgent and Emergency Care capacity: ClickMasters integrated with the NHS UEC Capacity Management system — real-time bed availability, waiting times at UTC/A&amp;E, and GP in-hours/out-of-hours availability. Disposition optimisation: if UTC waiting time &gt; 4 hours, alternative lower-acuity pathway offered where clinically appropriate. Ambulance dispatch integration: 999 disposition triggers CAD (Computer Aided Dispatch) pre-alert to ambulance trust.",
    "results": "DTAC approved all 5 domains. Platform live at 16 weeks, £82,000 — under budget. Call handling time: 8.4 minutes → 6.2 minutes average (26% reduction). ICD-10 coding accuracy: 88% top-1 suggestion accepted. NHS Pathways dispositions reviewed by clinical governance: 99.2% concordance with expected dispositions. WCAG 2.1 AA: zero non-compliances. IUC provider selected for NHS England digital exemplar programme based on platform performance.",
