    "title": "MedTech NHS Community Mental Health Digital Platform — IAPT Service",
    "metaTitle": "MedTech NHS Community Mental Health Digital Platform — IAPT Service — ClickMasters Case Study",
    "metaDesc": "An NHS Trust providing IAPT (Improving Access to Psychological Therapies) services to 28,000 patients per year...",
    "sector": "MedTech / Mental Health",
    "country": "UK",
    "status": "On Time",
    "contract": "Fixed Price",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "DTAC all 5 domains, DCB0129, NHS IAPT Data Standard, NHS Safe Messaging (Samaritans), UK GDPR Article 9, NHS DSP Toolkit, WCAG 2.1 AA, Cyber Essentials Plus",
    "challenge": "An NHS Trust providing IAPT (Improving Access to Psychological Therapies) services to 28,000 patients per year needed a digital platform — replacing paper-based referral triage, PHQ-9/GAD-7 questionnaire administration, therapist caseload management, and IAPT national data submission to NHS England. IAPT Data Standard (mandatory national reporting), DCB0129 (clinical safety in mental health — NHS Safe Messaging), DTAC all 5 domains, UK GDPR Article 9, NHS SDS, and WCAG 2.1 AA were mandatory. Budget: £80,000.",
    "approach": "IAPT Digital Referral and Triage: IAPT referral sources: GP referral (NHS eRS FHIR R4), self-referral (digital form), and third-party referral (A&amp;E, crisis). Triage workflow: referral received → PHQ-9 (depression) + GAD-7 (anxiety) questionnaires administered digitally → triage score calculated → severity band (mild/moderate/severe) → step allocation (Step 2 low-intensity, Step 3 high-intensity CBT, Step 4 specialist). Waiting time tracking: RTT (Referral to Treatment) clock from referral receipt — IAPT standard: first assessment within 6 weeks, first treatment within 18 weeks. PHQ-9 and GAD-7 Digital Administration: PHQ-9 (Patient Health Questionnaire-9) and GAD-7 (Generalised Anxiety Disorder-7): standardised validated questionnaires. Digital administration: 9 and 7 questions respectively, Likert scale responses (0–3), automatic scoring and severity banding. Session-by-session monitoring (SSM): PHQ-9/GAD-7 administered before each session — recovery tracking (reliable recovery = PHQ-9 &lt; 10 AND improvement ≥ 6). IAPT Data Standard: both instruments and scores mandated in national submission. NHS Safe Messaging and Mental Health Content: NHS Safe Messaging Guidelines (Samaritans): all IAPT platform content reviewed against safe messaging standards. No references to methods, no statistics that could normalise suicidal ideation. Safety planning: digital safety plan co-produced at first assessment — visible on patient's mobile app. Crisis resources: prominently displayed on every page (Samaritans 116 123, Crisis line, A&amp;E). NHS App Library: IAPT platforms must comply with NHS App Library standards if NHS App embedded. IAPT National Data Submission: IAPT Data Standard: quarterly submission to NHS England (NHS Digital CSDS — Community Services Data Set). Data extract: per-patient anonymised data (NHS number pseudonymised — SHA-256 hash), referral details, assessment outcomes, treatment sessions, recovery status. CSDS API: automated submission via NHS Digital CSDS API (NHS England Data Services). Data quality: automated data quality checks before submission — mandatory field completeness, valid code ranges, date logic.",
    "results": "DTAC approved all 5 domains. Platform live at 14 weeks, £74,000 — under budget. IAPT RTT compliance (first assessment within 6 weeks): 94% (target: 90%). Session-by-session monitoring completion: 96% (target: 85%). Reliable Recovery rate: 52% (above IAPT national average of 49%). IAPT Data Standard submission: automated — previously 3 days per quarter. WCAG 2.1 AA: zero non-compliances. NHS England praised the data quality as \"best in region\".",
