    "slug": "govtech-nhs-digital-maternity-record",
    "title": "GovTech NHS Digital Maternity Record — Integrated Care Board",
    "metaTitle": "GovTech NHS Digital Maternity Record — Integrated Care Board — ClickMasters Case Study",
    "metaDesc": "An NHS Integrated Care Board managing maternity services for 18,000 births per year across 3 acute trusts need...",
    "sector": "GovTech / NHS Maternity",
    "country": "UK",
    "status": "On Time",
    "contract": "Fixed Price",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "DTAC all 5 domains, DCB0129, NHS MDCR national programme, FHIR R4 Maternity IG, NHS Better Births, UK GDPR Article 9, NHS DSP Toolkit, WCAG 2.1 AA, Cyber Essentials Plus",
    "challenge": "An NHS Integrated Care Board managing maternity services for 18,000 births per year across 3 acute trusts needed a unified digital maternity record — replacing paper-based BadgerNet (legacy maternity system) with a FHIR R4-native digital platform. DTAC all 5 domains, DCB0129 (maternity is highest-risk clinical specialty — 50% of clinical negligence claims), NHS Maternity Digital Care Records (MDCRs — national programme), FHIR R4 (Maternity FHIR Implementation Guide), NHS England Better Births national requirements, and UK GDPR Article 9 were mandatory. Budget: £110,000.",
    "approach": "NHS Maternity FHIR R4 Implementation: NHS Maternity FHIR Implementation Guide: structured clinical records across pregnancy journey. Key FHIR resources: CarePlan (maternity care plan per pregnancy), Observation (blood pressure, urinalysis, fundal height, foetal heart rate), Procedure (antenatal appointments, scans, birth), Condition (obstetric diagnoses — gestational diabetes, pre-eclampsia), and Patient (mother) + RelatedPerson (baby). UK Core profiles: all FHIR resources validated against NHS UK Core R4 maternity profiles — SNOMED CT and dm+d codes. Booking appointment: first antenatal visit → full demographic and medical history → care plan created. DCB0129 Maternity Clinical Safety: Maternity is the highest-risk clinical specialty for clinical negligence (NHSLA — 50% of NHS litigation costs). Critical safety hazards in maternity records: (1) wrong gestation calculated → wrong management plan, mitigated by LMP-based calculation with sonographer confirmation, (2) missed high-risk flag → no consultant review, mitigated by automatic high-risk pathway trigger (BMI &gt;35, previous caesarean, GDM), (3) foetal movement reduction not acted on → foetal death, mitigated by RCOG guidance integration (Stillbirth &amp; Neonatal Death charity SANDS). NHS MDCR National Programme Integration: NHS England Maternity Digital Care Records (MDCRs) programme: national interoperability standard for maternity records — patient-held record accessible via NHS App. Platform: MDCR FHIR API (publish maternity record to NHS Spine → accessible via NHS App). Patient app: React Native PWA — mother can view her own maternity record, birth preferences, and scan reports. MDCR compliance: NHS England MDCR technical specification (published 2023) — structured data fields mapped to FHIR R4 resources. Antenatal Screening and Results Management: NHS antenatal screening: Down's syndrome, Edwards' and Patau's (combined test), spina bifida (nuchal translucency scan), sickle cell and thalassaemia, HIV, hepatitis B, rubella, and STIS. Results management: screening result → risk level → pathway trigger (high risk → referral to foetal medicine). Nuchal translucency measurement: FHIR Observation resource with SNOMED CT code, measurement value, gestational age at scan, and calculated risk ratio (combined test calculation).",
    "results": "DTAC approved all 5 domains. NHS MDCR compliance certified. Platform live at 20 weeks, £102,000 — under budget. 18,000 maternities per year supported across 3 trusts. NHS App maternity record access: 68% of pregnant women activated. DCGH2 (Saving Babies' Lives Version 3) compliance: platform integrates all 5 elements (foetal movement, CTG, smoking cessation, growth monitoring, umbilical artery Doppler). Clinical negligence risk reduction: Trust NHSLA assessment cited improved documentation as material risk reduction. WCAG 2.1 AA: zero non-compliances.",
