    "slug": "nhs-patient-flow-management",
    "title": "NHS Patient Flow Management Platform — UK Acute Trust",
    "metaTitle": "NHS Patient Flow Management Platform — UK Acute Trust — ClickMasters Case Study",
    "metaDesc": "An NHS Acute Trust with 620 beds and 72,000 emergency attendances per year wanted a real-time patient flow man...",
    "sector": "HealthTech / Patient Flow",
    "country": "UK",
    "status": "On Time",
    "contract": "Fixed Price",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "DTAC all 5 domains, DCB0129, NHS PAS FHIR R4, UK GDPR Article 9, NHS DSP Toolkit, WCAG 2.1 AA, Cyber Essentials Plus",
    "challenge": "An NHS Acute Trust with 620 beds and 72,000 emergency attendances per year wanted a real-time patient flow management platform — replacing whiteboards and Excel-based bed management. NHS DTAC all 5 domains, DCB0129 (patient flow errors directly cause delayed discharge and deterioration), NHS PAS (Patient Administration System) FHIR R4 integration, WCAG 2.1 AA, UK GDPR Article 9, and NHS DSP Toolkit were mandatory. Budget: £85,000.",
    "approach": "Real-Time Bed State Management: Bed state: every bed (620) has a current state (occupied/vacant/cleaning/blocked/maintenance). State changes: discharge triggers bed cleaning request (housekeeping team mobile app), cleaning complete triggers bed available for allocation, new admission triggers bed allocated. Real-time sync: WebSocket connection (Socket.IO) — all 34 ward displays, 8 bed managers, and 4 flow coordinators see bed state changes within 2 seconds. Prediction: machine learning discharge prediction (historical PAS data + length of stay model) — predicted discharges for next 4 hours shown per ward. NHS PAS Integration — FHIR R4: NHS Patient Administration System (PAS) integration: FHIR R4 Patient resource (demographics), Encounter resource (admission/discharge/transfer), and Location resource (ward/bay/bed). PAS systems: Meditech, System C Careflow, Cerner Millennium, Epic — each has FHIR R4 interface (HL7 FHIR Facade pattern for legacy PAS without native FHIR). Real-time ADT (Admission/Discharge/Transfer) events: PAS publishes HL7 v2 ADT messages → flow platform subscribes → FHIR R4 Encounter updated → bed state changed automatically. Delayed Transfer of Care Tracking: Delayed Transfer of Care (DTOC): patients medically fit for discharge but awaiting social care, package of care, or community bed. DTOC tracking: each patient flagged with reason code (Code 1: awaiting assessment, Code 2: awaiting public funding, Code 3: awaiting care home placement, Code 16: patient/family choice). DTOC dashboard: live DTOC count, reason distribution, average delay duration. NHS England DTOC reporting: automated daily submission to NHS England DTOC data collection. ClickMasters: DTOC data pipeline from flow platform to NHS England. DCB0129 Patient Flow Clinical Safety: Critical safety hazard: bed incorrectly shown as vacant → two admissions for same bed → patient safety incident. Mitigation: bed state is event-sourced (every state change has a user, timestamp, and audit trail), concurrent admission prevention (bed reservation lock for 10 minutes after allocation starts), and daily bed state audit (automated reconciliation against PAS ADT data — discrepancies alerted to bed manager). Second hazard: DTOC patient incorrectly discharged without care package in place. Mitigation: DTOC flag must be manually cleared with a named social care worker confirmation.",
    "results": "DTAC approved all 5 domains. Platform live at 14 weeks, £78,000 — under budget. Bed turnaround time (discharge to next admission): 4.8 hours → 2.6 hours (46% improvement). Delayed Transfer of Care: trust average DTOC days reduced from 8.4 to 6.1 days (NHS England target: &lt; 7). Emergency department 4-hour standard: improved from 68% to 74% (attributed to improved bed availability visibility). DTOC automated reporting: 100% (previously 2 days manual). NHS England DTOC benchmark: trust moved from bottom quartile to second quartile nationally.",
    "clientQuote": "",
