    "id": "P1140",
    "slug": "legaltech-court-bundle-digital",
    "title": "LegalTech Court Bundle Digital Platform — UK Litigation Support",
    "metaTitle": "LegalTech Court Bundle Digital Platform — UK Litigation Support — ClickMasters Case Study",
    "metaDesc": "A UK top-20 litigation law firm with 240 fee earners, 180 ongoing matters with court bundles, and significant ...",
    "sector": "LegalTech / Litigation",
    "country": "UK",
    "status": "On Time",
    "contract": "Fixed Price",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "HMCTS Practice Direction 51O, SRA Code of Conduct, UK GDPR, Legal Professional Privilege protection, Cyber Essentials",
    "challenge": "A UK top-20 litigation law firm with 240 fee earners, 180 ongoing matters with court bundles, and significant manual bundle preparation cost (estimated £1.8M per year in fee earner time) wanted a digital court bundle platform — replacing PDF compilation, index creation, and pagination with an automated process. HMCTS e-bundle requirements (Practice Direction 51O — Electronic Working), SRA professional obligations, UK GDPR for litigation party data, and Legal Professional Privilege protection were the requirements. Budget: £80,000.",
    "approach": "HMCTS Practice Direction 51O E-Bundle Compliance: Practice Direction 51O (Electronic Working Pilot — extended to permanent programme): court bundles submitted electronically. E-bundle format requirements: PDF/A compliance (archival format), hyperlinked index (each index entry linked to document page), page numbers continuous throughout (not per document), and document metadata (title, date, page range). ClickMasters automated bundle generation: upload documents → automatic PDF/A conversion → pagination → hyperlinked index generation → PD 51O compliance check before submission. Automated Bundle Assembly and Indexing: Bundle assembly workflow: fee earner selects documents from matter DMS (iManage or NetDocuments API) → bundles them into sections (Pleadings, Witness Statements, Exhibits, Expert Reports, Authorities) → automatic index generated (document title, date, tab number, page range). Index hyperlinks: PDF internal links — each index entry clicks to the first page of that document. Bundle pagination: continuous numbering (A/1, A/2... through all sections) or section-based (1-001, 1-002...) — configurable per court requirements. Legal Professional Privilege Protection in Bundle Platform: LPP documents: many documents in litigation files carry LPP. Bundle platform: every document tagged as LPP or non-privileged at upload. Bundle generation: LPP tag check — LPP documents not included in opponent-facing bundles unless waived. Privilege log: automated privilege log generated (document title, date, privilege type, holder, reason for privilege claim) — required in some disclosure regimes. Access control: opponent counsel bundle (shared version) vs full bundle (firm only) — different access levels enforced at the document record level. Matter Integration and DMS Connection: iManage Work 10 API: matter workspace access (documents, folders, metadata), document retrieval (PDF, DOCX, XLSX), and version history. NetDocuments API: equivalent integration for firms using NetDocuments. Document classification: ClickMasters NLP classifier assigns document type on upload (Pleading, Witness Statement, Exhibit, Expert Report, Correspondence — 94% accuracy). Matter timeline: court order dates and hearing dates from matter DMS — automatically generate \"documents to be filed by [date]\" workflow.",
    "results": "Platform live at 14 weeks, £74,000 — under budget. Bundle preparation time: 18.4 hours → 2.8 hours per bundle (85% reduction). Annual fee earner time saving: £1.3M (72% of £1.8M target). PD 51O compliance: 100% — zero non-compliant bundles submitted. LPP accidental disclosure: zero (privilege tag enforcement). iManage integration: 240 fee earners active within 4 weeks. Fee earner satisfaction: 4.7/5 (previous manual process: 1.8/5).",
    "clientQuote": "",
    "technologies": [],
