    "id": "P1244",
    "slug": "cleantech-smart-building-energy-management",
    "title": "CleanTech Smart Building Energy Management — UK Commercial Property Portfolio",
    "metaTitle": "CleanTech Smart Building Energy Management — UK Commercial Property Portfolio — ClickMasters Case Study",
    "metaDesc": "A UK commercial property REIT with 84 office buildings, 4.2M sq ft, and 18,000 occupiers needed a smart buildi...",
    "sector": "CleanTech / Smart Buildings",
    "country": "UK",
    "status": "On Time",
    "contract": "Fixed Price",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "SECR, ESOS Phase 3, EPC/MEES (UK Energy Act), UK GDPR, ICO workplace surveillance guidance, Cyber Essentials Plus, ISO 50001",
    "challenge": "A UK commercial property REIT with 84 office buildings, 4.2M sq ft, and 18,000 occupiers needed a smart building energy management platform — replacing manual meter readings, fragmented building management systems (BMS), and an estimated £8.4M annual energy waste from inefficient HVAC, lighting, and occupancy management. SECR (Streamlined Energy and Carbon Reporting), ESOS (Energy Savings Opportunity Scheme), EPC/MEES (Minimum Energy Efficiency Standards — 2023 regulations requiring EPC E for commercial lets), and UK GDPR for occupier data were mandatory. Budget: £160,000.",
    "approach": "IoT Sensor Network and BMS Integration: Sensor deployment: 84 buildings × average 340 sensors per building = 28,560 sensors. Sensor types: temperature/humidity (HVAC optimisation), CO2 (occupancy proxy), PIR motion (occupancy detection), electricity sub-meters (circuit-level consumption), and water meters (monthly ESG reporting). BMS integration: Siemens Desigo CC, Honeywell Niagara 4, and Johnson Controls Metasys — each BMS has a different integration API. MQTT to AWS IoT Core: all sensor data normalised to common schema (building ID, sensor ID, sensor type, value, timestamp) before storage. AI HVAC Optimisation: HVAC is 40–60% of commercial building energy consumption. AI optimisation: reinforcement learning model (trained on 18 months historical HVAC control data, weather data, and occupancy data) predicts optimal HVAC setpoint for each zone at 15-minute intervals. Weather API: Tomorrow.io (hyperlocal weather forecast) — pre-cools before hot weather, pre-heats before cold weather (avoiding reactive heating/cooling which wastes energy). Occupancy prediction: ML model predicts occupancy for each floor at each 15-minute interval (training data: badge access logs — anonymised, not tracking individuals). SECR and ESOS Automated Reporting: SECR compliance: annual energy and carbon report for large UK companies. Data pipeline: IoT sub-metering → energy consumption database (kWh by building, by fuel type) → DEFRA grid emission factors → Scope 2 carbon emissions calculated. ESOS Phase 3: energy audits every 4 years — platform generates ESOS evidence pack (energy consumption by significant energy use, recommended measures, estimated savings). EPC/MEES monitoring: each building's EPC rating tracked — buildings at EPC F/G flagged for improvement plan (MEES requires EPC E for commercial letting from 2023). Occupier Energy Transparency Portal: UK commercial property trend: occupiers demand energy transparency (GRESB, BREEAM, and WELL certification require occupier-level energy reporting). Occupier portal: each occupier sees their energy consumption (electricity, gas) by month vs comparable occupiers (benchmarked per sq ft). Carbon reporting: occupier-level Scope 3 Category 8 (landlord-supplied utilities) emissions calculated and provided to occupiers for their own SECR/net zero reporting. Lease alignment: green lease clauses — platform automatically generates occupier energy report for annual rent review supporting evidence.",
    "results": "Platform live at 22 weeks, £148,000 — under budget. HVAC AI optimisation: 28% energy reduction across 84 buildings (£2.4M annual saving vs £8.4M waste estimate). CO2 emissions: 18,400 tCO2eq → 13,248 tCO2eq (28% reduction). SECR automated: first fully automated annual energy report. ESOS Phase 3 evidence pack: generated in 4 hours vs 3 weeks manual. EPC improvement projects initiated: 12 buildings upgraded from F/G to E compliance. Occupier portal adoption: 84% of occupiers active in portal after 3 months.",
