    "title": "InsurTech Personal Lines Telematics Insurance Platform — UK Insurer",
    "metaTitle": "InsurTech Personal Lines Telematics Insurance Platform — UK Insurer — ClickMasters Case Study",
    "metaDesc": "A UK FCA-authorised personal lines insurer with 280,000 motor policies and an existing black box telematics pr...",
    "sector": "InsurTech / Telematics",
    "country": "UK",
    "status": "On Time",
    "contract": "Fixed Price",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "FCA ICOBS, FCA Consumer Duty (PS22/9), UK GDPR (telematics location data), ICO telematics guidance, PCI-DSS SAQ-A, Apple ATT, Google Data Safety, Cyber Essentials Plus",
    "challenge": "A UK FCA-authorised personal lines insurer with 280,000 motor policies and an existing black box telematics programme (2G device — being decommissioned by MNOs) needed to build a next-generation smartphone telematics platform — replacing the physical black box with a mobile SDK, providing drivers with real-time feedback, and enabling usage-based insurance (UBI) with live pricing adjustments. FCA ICOBS (personal lines motor insurance), FCA Consumer Duty PS22/9, UK GDPR (telematics location data is personal data), ICO guidance on telematics and employment monitoring, PCI-DSS (premium payment), and App Store / Play Store data privacy requirements were mandatory. Budget: £150,000.",
    "approach": "Mobile SDK Telematics Data Collection: React Native SDK (iOS + Android): trip detection (accelerometer + GPS — detects journey start/end automatically), driving behaviour scoring (harsh braking via accelerometer, cornering via gyroscope, speed via GPS vs HERE Maps speed limit data, phone handling via motion sensor). Privacy by design: precise GPS coordinates anonymised at collection (stored as speed + road segment, not precise location), trip data stored on device for 30 minutes then uploaded to server (device-side anonymisation). ICO telematics guidance: location data is personal data under UK GDPR — privacy notice explicitly describes telematics data collection, frequency, and purpose. Real-Time Driving Score and Feedback: Driving score: composite score (harsh braking 30%, cornering 20%, speed 30%, phone handling 20%) calculated per trip and aggregated monthly. Real-time feedback: post-trip notification (overall score, worst event during trip with advice — \"You braked sharply twice — try to increase following distance\"). Gamification: weekly leaderboard (anonymous — drivers opt in), monthly rewards for high scorers (premium discount or voucher). FCA Consumer Duty: driving feedback must be fair, clear, and not misleading — score criteria disclosed in app. Vulnerable customers: drivers who flag anxiety around driving performance excluded from leaderboard and comparative features. Usage-Based Insurance Pricing: UBI pricing: base premium + driving score adjustment (±20% of base premium based on monthly driving score) + mileage adjustment (annual mileage estimate refined by actual GPS mileage). FCA ICOBS: UBI pricing must be transparent — driver can see exactly how their score affects their premium (itemised premium statement). FCA Consumer Duty value assessment: is UBI fair value for low-mileage, high-scoring drivers? Annual value assessment: compare UBI premium vs equivalent non-telematics premium for all customer segments. Underwriting: telematics data shared with reinsurer (in anonymised aggregate) — individual-level data not shared without explicit consent. App Store Compliance — Apple ATT and Google Data Safety: Apple App Tracking Transparency (ATT): telematics app uses location in background (continuous GPS) — iOS requires permission prompt explaining location use. App Privacy Label: location data (precise GPS — collected), driving behaviour (collected), device identifiers (not collected). Google Play Data Safety: location data (precise, approximate — purpose: telematics scoring and UBI pricing), app activity (trip data — collected). ICO UK GDPR: App Store privacy labels must be accurate and match actual data collection — ICO enforces UK GDPR compliance for mobile apps.",
    "results": "FCA ICOBS compliance confirmed. App live at 20 weeks, £138,000 — under budget. App Store launch: 4.2 stars iOS, 4.1 stars Android. Active telematics users: 84,000 (30% of 280,000 policy base) in first 6 months. Average driving score: 74/100. Claims frequency for telematics customers: 18% lower than non-telematics equivalent (underwriting benefit — telematics selects better drivers). FCA Consumer Duty review: confirmed compliant. Customer average UBI premium saving: £84/year. ICO telematics assessment: zero findings.",
