    "slug": "retailtech-luxury-fashion-dtc-platform",
    "title": "RetailTech Luxury Fashion Direct-to-Consumer Platform — UK Brand",
    "metaTitle": "RetailTech Luxury Fashion Direct-to-Consumer Platform — UK Brand — ClickMasters Case Study",
    "metaDesc": "A UK luxury fashion brand with £84M annual revenue, 340,000 registered customers, and a legacy Magento 1 platf...",
    "sector": "RetailTech / Luxury DTC",
    "country": "UK",
    "status": "On Time",
    "contract": "Fixed Price",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "UK GDPR, PECR, Consumer Rights Act 2015, Consumer Contracts Regulations 2013, PCI-DSS SAQ-A, WCAG 2.1 AA, Cyber Essentials",
    "challenge": "A UK luxury fashion brand with £84M annual revenue, 340,000 registered customers, and a legacy Magento 1 platform (end-of-life since 2020) needed to build a modern direct-to-consumer (DTC) platform — providing personalised shopping, same-day London delivery, virtual styling appointments, and international e-commerce. UK GDPR, PECR (email marketing consent), Consumer Rights Act (luxury goods returns), PCI-DSS SAQ-A, WCAG 2.1 AA (Equality Act compliance), and Apple Pay/Google Pay integration were mandatory. Budget: £160,000.",
    "approach": "Headless Commerce Architecture: Headless architecture: Shopify Plus (product catalogue, inventory, checkout, order management) + custom Next.js 14 App Router frontend (full visual control, luxury brand experience, Core Web Vitals). Shopify Storefront API: product queries, collection queries, variant selection. Shopify Checkout Extensions: custom luxury experience (gift message, delivery preference, complimentary gift wrapping). Core Web Vitals: LCP 1.2s (CloudFront CDN + Next.js ISR for product pages), INP &lt; 100ms, CLS 0. Apple Pay and Google Pay: Shopify Payments (PCI-DSS SAQ-A — Stripe behind Shopify) with Apple Pay and Google Pay enabled. Personalisation and Virtual Styling: Customer profile: purchase history, size preferences (configurable per category — UK size 10 in dresses, US 6 in jeans), colour preferences, style preferences (classic, contemporary, avant-garde). Personalised product feed: collaborative filtering (customers like you purchased) + content-based filtering (similar to items you have purchased) + editorial curation (buyer team seasonal picks). Virtual styling appointment: Calendly integration (book 45-minute video call with personal stylist), Whereby video (GDPR-compliant EU data residency), pre-appointment questionnaire (style, occasion, budget). Post-appointment: personalised lookbook generated by stylist (React component, shared via link). UK Consumer Rights Act Returns: Consumer Rights Act 2015 + Consumer Contracts Regulations 2013: 14-day right to withdraw for online luxury purchases (luxury goods — no exclusion). Returns workflow: (1) return initiated online (within 14 days, tracked), (2) pre-paid returns label generated (Royal Mail Tracked Returns API — QR code emailed), (3) item received at returns centre (CCTV evidence of condition check for luxury items — consumer law requires condition evidence for deduction claims), (4) refund processed within 14 days. Luxury damage assessment: photos uploaded at returns centre + automated comparison to original condition photos (AI image comparison — damage deduction workflow if condition change). PECR Consent and Email Marketing: PECR (Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulations): email marketing to existing customers (soft opt-in for similar products — PECR regulation 22(3)(b)), new subscribers require explicit opt-in. Consent capture: Klaviyo + OneTrust integration (consent status stored in Klaviyo profile — audit trail of consent). Email preference centre: granular consent (new arrivals, sale, editorial, event invitations — all separately toggled). Automated flows: abandoned cart (only sent to explicit opt-in subscribers), post-purchase (order confirmation — transactional, no consent needed), review request (14 days post-delivery — transactional). GDPR data retention: inactive subscriber data deleted after 24 months (automated Klaviyo suppression).",
    "results": "Platform live at 18 weeks, £148,000 — under budget. Magento 1 decommissioned day 1 of go-live (zero legacy overlap). Core Web Vitals: LCP 1.2s (vs Magento 1.8s), INP 84ms, CLS 0 — all green. Revenue in first 6 months: £52M (vs £38M same period previous year — 37% uplift, multi-factor). Personalised product feed: 42% of sessions use recommended products. Virtual styling appointments: 840 booked in first 6 months (average order value: £1,840 vs site average £380). Returns rate: 22.4% (industry average luxury: 28%). WCAG 2.1 AA: zero critical non-compliances.",
