    "compliance": "UKRI reporting requirements, Horizon Europe AMGA, Charity Commission requirements, HEFCE TRAC, UK GDPR (researcher data), WCAG 2.1 AA, Cyber Essentials Plus",
    "challenge": "A UK Russell Group university with £840M annual research income, 4,200 active research grants, and 2,800 researchers needed a unified research grant management platform — replacing a combination of legacy ResearchFish, manual UKRI (UK Research and Innovation) reporting, and spreadsheet-based financial management. UKRI reporting requirements, Horizon Europe (UK-EU collaboration), Royal Society, Wellcome Trust, and charity funder reporting, Charity Commission requirements (for externally funded research), UK GDPR for researcher data, and WCAG 2.1 AA were mandatory. Budget: £160,000.",
    "approach": "UKRI Research Portfolio Management: UKRI (UK Research and Innovation — EPSRC, AHRC, BBSRC, ESRC, MRC, NERC, Innovate UK): UK's primary public research funder. UKRI Flexi Grant API: application and grant management via UKRI Flexi Grant system. Platform integration: (1) UKRI grant award import (award details, budget breakdown, start/end dates), (2) researcher portal (PI — Principal Investigator — views their grants, milestones, budget remaining), (3) ResearchFish integration (annual UKRI reporting tool — outcomes and impact data — UKRI Flexi Grant API exports to ResearchFish), (4) UKRI Financial Reporting (JeS — Joint Electronic Submission — financial returns), (5) UKRI Peer Review (UKRI funding applications — ClickMasters builds application submission workflow). Horizon Europe and International Funding: Horizon Europe: EU research funding programme — UK associated country (post-Brexit, UK is associated from 2024). Horizon Europe Grant Agreement: EU financial regulation compliance (EC Audit requirements, AMGA — Model Grant Agreement), PI eligibility checks (UK researchers can lead Horizon projects as of 2024 association). Portal: Horizon Europe grants managed alongside UKRI grants — unified view of all funding. F&amp;A (Facilities and Administration) calculation: Horizon Europe overhead rate (25% for indirect costs — different from UKRI FEC). EU audit trail: Horizon Europe grants subject to EC audit — immutable financial records required (7-year retention). EURAXESS: researcher mobility tracking (UK-EU researcher movement for Horizon projects). Research Financial Management and FEC: FEC (Full Economic Costing): UK universities use fEC to calculate the true cost of research (direct costs + indirect costs + overhead). fEC components: (1) directly incurred costs (staff, travel, equipment), (2) directly allocated costs (estates, library — apportioned to project), (3) indirect costs (central university overheads — calculated as overhead rate × direct staff costs). Financial reporting: TRAC (Transparent Approach to Costing — HEFCE requirement): annual cost return to HEFCE. Research financial dashboard: project budget utilisation (% of fEC budget spent), forecast to completion (will project underspend or overspend?), staff costs (FTE against grant — UKRI staffing rules). Charity Accounts (Charity Commission): separate accounting for charities funding research (Wellcome Trust, British Heart Foundation). Research Impact and REF Preparation: REF (Research Excellence Framework): UK research assessment — determines HEIF (Higher Education Innovation Fund) allocation. REF 2029 preparation: platform tracks research impact evidence (citations, policy influence, societal impact — Impact Case Study data). ORCID integration: researcher ORCID (Open Researcher and Contributor ID — unique researcher identifier) linked to all research outputs. CRIS (Current Research Information System): PURE (Elsevier) or Symplectic Elements data exchange — publication metadata (DOI, journal, authors) imported for REF submission. Open Access compliance: UKRI open access mandate (all UKRI-funded publications must be open access within 12 months) — compliance tracking per publication.",
    "results": "UKRI compliance confirmed. Platform live at 24 weeks, £148,000 — under budget. 4,200 research grants across UKRI, Horizon Europe, and charity funders. UKRI ResearchFish completion rate: 94.2% (UKRI minimum: 80%). Horizon Europe financial compliance: confirmed by EC audit (no findings). fEC budget utilisation variance: &lt; 2.4% (target: &lt; 5%). REF impact evidence captured: 84% of active grants have Impact Case Study data (target: 70%). Open Access compliance: 92.4% of UKRI publications open access within mandate. Researcher satisfaction: 4.3/5.",
