    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "HMLR Digital Street, TPO verification, UK GDPR, ICO AADC, PECR, SDLT regulations, PCI-DSS SAQ-A, WCAG 2.1 AA, Cyber Essentials",
    "challenge": "A UK property search startup building a competing search platform to Rightmove and Zoopla needed to build a consumer-grade property search experience — with HMLR data integration, agent onboarding, and a distinctive first-time buyer feature set. HMLR Digital Street APIs, TPO (The Property Ombudsman) agent verification, ICO AADC (some first-time buyer users are under 18), UK GDPR, PCI-DSS SAQ-A (premium subscription), PECR, and WCAG 2.1 AA were mandatory. Budget: £130,000.",
    "approach": "Property Search Architecture and HMLR Integration: Property search core: (1) listing database (PostgreSQL with PostGIS — geospatial search by radius from postcode), (2) HMLR Price Paid Data integration (30M+ historical UK property transactions — \"sold price\" feature, updated monthly), (3) HMLR INSPIRE Polygons (property boundary polygons — displayed on map overlay), (4) EPC Register integration (energy rating displayed on every listing — automated lookup by UPRN), (5) flood risk overlay (Environment Agency API — flood zone 1/2/3 displayed on map for each property). Search ranking: Elasticsearch (full-text search — property description, location name, postcode area). UPRN as primary property identifier throughout — cross-references HMLR, EPC, VOA, flood risk data for each property. Agent Onboarding and TPO Verification: Estate agent onboarding: 16,000 estate agency branches in the UK — all must verify TPO membership before listing. TPO (The Property Ombudsman) verification: (1) TPO firm ID lookup (TPO public register API — verify firm is TPO member), (2) HMRC VAT number verification (VAT validation API — confirm estate agency is registered business), (3) AML verification (MLRs 2017 — estate agents are Supervised Persons — identity verification for onboarding agent staff), (4) Propertymark membership check (NAEA Propertymark — additional quality signal). Agent portal: estate agent onboards (submits TPO ID), ClickMasters verifies, agent gains access to listing API. Integration: Rightmove RTDF and Zoopla ZPF export — agent can list on ClickMasters platform simultaneously with Rightmove/Zoopla. First-Time Buyer Feature Set: First-time buyer differentiation: (1) Stamp Duty Land Tax calculator (SDLT — first-time buyer relief up to £425,000 — automated SDLT calculation at search price), (2) Help to Buy calculator (historical scheme — equity loan calculator for eligible properties), (3) mortgage affordability estimate (income × 4.5 = indicative mortgage, displayed on every property), (4) school checker (Ofsted school ratings by postcode — Good/Outstanding schools within 1 mile), (5) commute calculator (Google Maps Distance Matrix API — commute time from property to user's workplace), (6) first-time buyer guide (educational content — stamp duty, conveyancing, surveys, mortgages). AADC: under-18 users who may be researching family home purchases — AADC data minimisation applied. Performance Architecture for Property Search: Property search LCP optimisation: users expect Rightmove-level performance. Architecture: (1) Elasticsearch (sub-100ms search response for any UK postcode), (2) Redis (hot property listings — recently viewed, recently listed — sub-5ms), (3) CloudFront (property photos served from S3 via CDN — global edge), (4) Next.js ISR (Incremental Static Regeneration — property listing pages statically generated, invalidated on price change or status change), (5) WebSocket (real-time new listing alerts — user receives notification within 60 seconds of new property matching their search). Core Web Vitals: LCP &lt; 1.5s on property search results (Rightmove: 2.8s — significant competitive advantage). Mobile-first: 72% of UK property search is mobile.",
    "results": "Platform live at 22 weeks, £122,000 — under budget. 420,000 property listings from 1,800 agent branches. HMLR Price Paid: 30M transactions integrated. EPC display: 100% of listings. LCP: 1.3s (Rightmove: 2.8s). Core Web Vitals: all green. WCAG 2.1 AA: zero non-compliances. TPO verification: 100% of agents. SDLT calculator: 42% of users use on every property (most-used feature). Commute calculator: 38% of users. School checker: 34% of users. ICO AADC: confirmed compliant. First-time buyer conversion: 28% higher than competitor average (product research).",
