    "approach": "AST Digital Workflow: (1) tenant application (income verification, credit check via Experian API, employment reference), (2) Right to Rent check (GOV.UK share code for non-UK nationals, document upload for UK nationals), (3) AST generation (automated -- Homes Act compliance clauses included), (4) e-signature (DocuSign), (5) deposit registration (TDS API -- mandatory within 30 days). CMA guidelines: AST terms reviewed against CMA unfair terms -- prohibited clauses removed. Right to Rent Compliance: (1) GOV.UK Right to Rent online service -- share code verification, (2) document-based check (passport, BRP, visa -- scanned and uploaded), (3) time-limited right tracking (visa expiry -- 90-day automated reminder), (4) record keeping (tenancy duration + 1 year), (5) Home Office reporting (if check fails -- reporting obligation). Right to Rent failure does not give automatic right to evict -- lawful eviction process required. TDS Deposit Protection: (1) deposit received via GoCardless -- ring-fenced, (2) TDS REST API auto-registration on receipt, (3) Deposit Protection Certificate to tenant (GOV.UK Notify), (4) Prescribed Information within 30 days, (5) check-out deductions (inventory report, TDS arbitration for disputes). Housing Act 2004: failure to register within 30 days = 3x deposit fine. BTR Tenant Portal: (1) rent payment (GoCardless VRP -- monthly bank-to-bank), (2) maintenance requests (React Native -- photo + description, priority triage), (3) maintenance tracking (GOV.UK Notify status updates), (4) document vault (AST, deposit certificate, house manual), (5) community board (opt-in, GDPR consent required). Homes Act category 1 hazard (damp, mould, heating failure): automatic emergency 24-hour SLA.",
