    "approach": "Electronic Manifest and Pre-Arrival: (1) shipping line API (SOLAS-compliant manifest via REST), (2) manifest validation (commodity codes, IMDG dangerous goods), (3) UK Border Force ENS generation (automated from manifest), (4) pre-arrival risk assessment (HMRC automated), (5) vessel tracking (Vesseltracker AIS API -- 10-minute updates). 24-hour rule compliance: manifest submission time recorded, non-compliant flagged. Berth Planning and Vessel Scheduling: (1) berth availability calendar (LOA limit, draft limit, cargo type), (2) vessel booking (IMO number, ETD, cargo volume), (3) automated berth allocation (beam + LOA + tidal window + crane availability), (4) port resources planning (pilot, tugs, mooring), (5) AIS ETA update (automated resource team notification 4 hours before arrival). MCA tidal prediction integration for LOA tidal window constraints. HMRC CDS Port Integration: (1) Frontier Declaration (CDS procedure 01 -- goods entering UK), (2) temporary storage procedures, (3) release notification (goods cleared -- release to quayside), (4) duty deferment (DDA balance check), (5) ETSF weekly HMRC report. Agent authorisation: each freight forwarder has own EORI -- PCS handles CDS on behalf of 280 forwarders. Freight Forwarder Portal: 280 companies each with self-service portal: (1) cargo status (vessel arrived, discharged, customs cleared, available), (2) document upload (bill of lading, commercial invoice, certificate of origin), (3) HMRC CDS status, (4) collection time-slot booking (number plate recognition gate), (5) automated invoicing (port dues, handling, storage per TEU per day). PostgreSQL RLS isolates forwarder data.",
    "results": "Platform live at 26 weeks, GBP148,000. 2.4M TEU. Pre-arrival 100% digital (was 40% paper). CDS release automated. Berth 100% digital. Dwell time 2.4 to 0.8 days. 94.2% of 280 forwarders active within 60 days. WCAG zero.",
