    "approach": "ESFA ILR Automation: Monthly automated ILR submission (R01-R14): learner ULN, demographics, learning aims, employment outcomes, achievements. ESFA Learner Register API: ULN verification before submission (invalid ULN = funding recovery risk). At-risk dashboard: low attendance, no engagement, poor outcomes flagged for early intervention. Ofsted CIF Digital Evidence: (1) learner journey evidence (anonymised case studies from platform data), (2) real-time attendance (Ofsted inspectors review patterns), (3) SAR data (pass rates, achievement rates, satisfaction), (4) observation records (lesson observations with Ofsted graded records), (5) destination data (6-month employment follow-up via GOV.UK Notify). Ofsted readiness pack generated on demand. Learner Portal and AADC: AADC compliance (16-18 learners under-18): behavioural analytics off by default, social features opt-in. Portal: timetable, attendance logging, learning resources (Moodle LTI 1.3), assignment submission (Turnitin LTI 1.3), bursary management (16-19 Bursary Fund eligibility check). Attendance target 90% (ESFA funding condition) -- automated alert to personal tutor. GCSE Resit Integration: Mandatory ESFA Condition of Funding: learners without Grade 4+ GCSE English/Maths must continue studying. (1) Initial diagnostic assessment, (2) Functional Skills or GCSE resit allocation, (3) progress tracking, (4) AQA/Pearson/OCR EDI submission (exam entry, grade processing), (5) automated Condition of Funding compliance report.",
