    "challenge": "UK community pharmacy chain (280 dispensing sites, 8.4M items/year) needed to modernise dispensing management. NHS EPS R3, NHS DTAC all 5 domains, DCB0129 (dispensing errors = clinical safety incidents), CQC, GPhC, HSCN, UK GDPR Article 9, WCAG 2.1 AA. Budget GBP130,000.",
    "approach": "NHS EPS R3 Integration: EPS R3: electronic prescriptions from GP to pharmacy. (1) prescription download (pharmacy nominates -- EPS Token API), (2) dispensing claim (NHSBSA FP10 claim -- GBP9.90 dispensing fee per item 2024/25), (3) cancellation handling (GP cancels before dispensing), (4) repeat dispensing (multiple EPS tokens), (5) controlled drugs (Schedule 2/3 -- EPS CD prescriptions require paper signature for Schedule 2). Monthly FP10 claim automated to NHS BSA. MDS Barcode Verification: MDS (Monitored Dosage System): blister pack compliance aids for complex patients. Critical DCB0129 hazard: wrong medication in blister. Mitigation: barcode verification required at each MDS dispensing step -- scanner prevents wrong drug from being placed in blister. System: each medication scanned against prescription before placement. MDS schedule: which medications, which times, which days -- automated from GP repeat prescriptions. DCB0129 Pharmacy Safety: Critical hazards and mitigations: (1) wrong drug -- barcode scan at dispensing, patient identity check before handout, (2) wrong dose -- dose check display (prescribed vs dispensed), (3) expired medication -- batch/expiry tracking (alert if expiry within 7 days), (4) allergy not checked -- NHS GP Connect allergy data at dispensing (automated alert if allergy match), (5) controlled drug error -- CD register, dual pharmacist verification for Schedule 2. CQC and GPhC Compliance: (1) SOPs digital library (CQC -- version control for all dispensing SOPs), (2) CD register (Schedule 2 -- running balance, dual checks, GPhC regulation), (3) near-miss reporting (GPhC quality improvement), (4) clinical audit (quarterly), (5) CPD records (GPhC pharmacist records). Companies House verification for new pharmacy owner GPhC registration.",
    "results": "NHS DTAC approved all 5 domains. Platform live at 22 weeks, GBP122,000. 280 sites. 8.4M items/year. EPS R3 automated (NHS BSA FP10 claims). MDS barcode verification 100%. Dispensing error rate 0.014% vs GPhC target 0.1%. 284 near-misses captured year one. CD dual verification 100%. CQC: Inadequate to Good. WCAG zero.",
