    "approach": "LTI 1.3 Advantage Integration: LTI 1.3 + NRPS + AGS: (1) Turnitin LTI (plagiarism detection), (2) Panopto LTI (lecture capture), (3) MATLAB Grader LTI (engineering simulations), (4) Kortext LTI (digital textbooks), (5) Teksynap LTI (online exams). LTI Advantage NRPS: each tool queries enrolled students from VLE. LTI Advantage AGS: Turnitin posts grades back to VLE gradebook automatically. IMS Global LTI 1.3 Certified -- required for JISC procurement frameworks. SITS OneRoster Integration: SITS (Student Information and Timetabling System): UK HE standard (60% of UK universities). OneRoster 1.1 REST from SITS: orgs (faculties), users (students/staff), classes (modules), enrollments. Nightly sync for standard periods. Critical periods (clearing, Fresher week): near-real-time WebSocket pattern from SITS. UK-specific fields: UK student ID, UCAS entry year, disability flags (WCAG 2.1 AA prioritisation). JISC Janet Network and Cyber Essentials: JISC Janet-specific: (1) data flows within Janet (JISC data classification), (2) Eduroam integration (Shibboleth SAML 2.0 for single sign-on), (3) OpenAthens federated identity, (4) JISC DDoS protection, (5) CE Plus (required for all software services sold to UK universities via JISC procurement). All student data processed within Janet-connected UK infrastructure. WCAG and ICO AADC for University VLE: WCAG 2.1 AA for 42,000 students: axe-playwright automated scan, NVDA + JAWS screen reader testing, keyboard navigation, Panopto auto-captions, React Native mobile accessibility. ICO AADC for under-18 foundation students: behavioural analytics off by default, learning analytics opt-in for under-18, no marketing profiling.",
