    "approach": "Companies House REST API v3.0: (1) Company search (name or number), (2) company profile (address, SIC codes, status, incorporation), (3) officers (directors, secretaries, appointments), (4) PSC persons with significant control (beneficial ownership), (5) filing history (all filed documents). OAuth 2.0 for write operations, API key for read-only. Rate limits: 600 requests per 5 minutes. Director personal data (name, birth month/year, nationality) is public under Companies Act 2006. Companies House Filing API: Supported filings: (1) Company formation (IN01 -- name, office, directors, shares, SIC), (2) Confirmation statement (CS01 -- annual -- shareholder details, SIC update), (3) Annual accounts (AA -- micro-entity, small, full -- iXBRL), (4) Director appointment (AP01), director termination (TM01), (5) Registered office change (AD01). iXBRL: Companies House accepts inline XBRL tagged accounts. Auto-reminder via GOV.UK Notify 2 weeks before confirmation statement due. HMRC MTD Corporation Tax: MTD CT mandatory for accounting periods starting April 2026. MTD CT API: obligation periods, CT600 digital submission, payment API, tax position. iXBRL accounts: same tagged accounts used for both Companies House and HMRC CT600 -- single generation workflow. ClickMasters builds iXBRL from structured P&amp;L and balance sheet data. UK GDPR for Director Personal Data: Director data at Companies House is public (Companies Act 2006). However: (1) home address suppression (directors can suppress -- service address shown publicly), (2) DOB suppression (month/year only public), (3) legitimate interest for due diligence processing, (4) PECR applies to marketing use without consent, (5) SAR: individuals can request removal where data is inaccurate or they qualify for suppression. ClickMasters accountancy SaaS: purpose limitation, retention policy, suppression support.",
