    "compliance": "FCA Regulatory Sandbox, FCA ICOBS (post-Sandbox), FCA Consumer Duty, ICO DPIA, ICO PECR, MID (MIBI), UK GDPR, WCAG 2.1 AA, Cyber Essentials",
    "challenge": "UK InsurTech building pay-per-mile motor insurance via smartphone telematics under FCA Regulatory Sandbox. FCA Sandbox (Innovation Hub -- temporary authorisation), FCA ICOBS (post-Sandbox), FCA Consumer Duty, ICO PECR (location tracking), ICO DPIA (continuous GPS monitoring), MID (Motor Insurance Database), UK GDPR, WCAG 2.1 AA. Budget GBP110,000.",
    "approach": "FCA Regulatory Sandbox Application: FCA Sandbox allows testing innovative products with real customers under temporary authorisation -- without 12-18 month full FCA authorisation. Application: (1) innovation case (pay-per-mile via pure smartphone telematics -- genuinely new at UK scale), (2) consumer safeguards (insurance cover day 1, cancellation rights, complaints), (3) test parameters (2,000 customers, 6-month period, success metrics), (4) exit plan (full FCA ICOBS authorisation after Sandbox). FCA Sandbox accepted: 3-month review, 6-month test period. Pay-Per-Mile Telematics Platform: iOS CoreMotion + GPS: trip start/end detection, mileage measured to 0.1 miles. GoCardless VRP: variable monthly billing based on miles. Dashboard: miles driven, cost accrued, projected bill. FCA Consumer Duty: actuarial evidence that pay-per-mile genuinely saves money for low-mileage drivers vs standard annual premium. Analysis: 34.2% average saving for drivers under 6,000 miles/year (60% of UK drivers). MID Integration: MID (MIBI API): (1) policy inception within 24 hours (MID POST), (2) mileage-based policy -- standard MID fields, (3) policy suspension (vehicle SORN -- MID updated), (4) policy cancellation (MID DELETE within 24 hours). DVLA ANPR enforcement: zero MID gaps -- every day uninsured is a DVLA enforcement risk for the customer. ICO DPIA for UBI: DPIA mandatory (Article 35 -- continuous GPS monitoring): (1) purpose limitation (location for mileage + driving score only -- not shared without consent), (2) data minimisation (GPS track stored 30 days post-trip only -- deleted after mileage billed), (3) PECR consent (explicit opt-in -- granular: mileage only vs mileage + score), (4) accuracy rights (customer can dispute mileage -- GPS track review mechanism), (5) annual DPIA review. High risk -- annual review required.",
    "results": "FCA Sandbox authorisation obtained. Platform live at 20 weeks, GBP102,000. 2,000 Sandbox customers. Pay-per-mile billing: 100% automated GoCardless VRP. MID: 100% within 24 hours. ICO DPIA filed. PECR consent 96.4%. Average 34.2% saving for low-mileage drivers. Consumer Duty actuarial evidence confirmed. Post-Sandbox: full ICOBS authorisation application submitted.",
