    "title": "FinTech UK Pension Platform -- Pensions Dashboard Programme",
    "metaTitle": "FinTech UK Pension Platform -- Pensions Dashboard Programme -- ClickMasters Case Study",
    "metaDesc": "A UK FCA-authorised pensions provider (280,000 members, GBP4.2B AUM) needed to integrate with the UK Pensions ...",
    "sector": "",
    "country": "",
    "status": "",
    "contract": "",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "PDP Connect (MaPS PDP Standards), FCA COBS, The Pensions Regulator (TPR), HMRC pension tax relief, UK GDPR, ISO 27001, Cyber Essentials Plus",
    "challenge": "A UK FCA-authorised pensions provider (280,000 members, GBP4.2B AUM) needed to integrate with the UK Pensions Dashboard Programme (PDP) -- the government initiative giving UK citizens a single view of all their pensions. PDP Connect (ATLAS staging and live connection), MaPS PDP Standards (PDP API standards -- OIDC, FHIR-inspired), FCA COBS pension transfer rules, The Pensions Regulator (TPR), HMRC pension API, UK GDPR (pension data is sensitive financial data), Cyber Essentials Plus, ISO 27001. Budget GBP130,000.",
    "approach": "PDP Connect Integration: PDP (Pensions Dashboard Programme) Connect: government-mandated pension finder service. PDP ATLAS staging: (1) ATLAS (API Testing and Lookup Service) -- all pension providers must connect via ATLAS, (2) PDP Standards (MaPS -- Money and Pensions Service publishes PDP Standards -- OpenAPI 3.0 based), (3) Find request (dashboard sends Find request with individual identity -- name, DOB, NI number), (4) Data request (dashboard sends Data request for pension details -- benefit statement, estimated retirement income), (5) View response (pension provider returns pension details in PDP standard format -- accrued benefits, estimated values). PDP go-live: staged rollout 2025-2026 -- pension providers connecting in waves by provider type. ClickMasters supported ATLAS staging connection and live connection. PDP Data Standards and Pension Benefit Statements: PDP data standards: pension benefit statement in PDP format. Defined benefit (DB) pensions: (1) accrued pension at normal retirement date, (2) transfer value, (3) date of joining, (4) normal pension age. Defined contribution (DC) pensions: (1) current pot value, (2) projected pot at retirement (MaPS projection standards), (3) transfer value, (4) contribution rate. PDP projection standards: MaPS specifies projection assumptions (investment growth, charges, mortality) -- providers must use MaPS assumptions for PDP projections (not their own). SMPI (Statutory Money Purchase Illustration): annual SMPI -- same projection assumptions now used for PDP dashboard projections (consistency). HMRC Pension Tax Relief API: HMRC pension tax relief: (1) relief at source (RAS -- ClickMasters pension platform claims basic rate tax relief from HMRC on behalf of members), (2) HMRC RAS API (monthly claim submission -- contribution data to HMRC), (3) HMRC MTD for pensions (HMRC digitisation programme -- pension providers must submit digitally), (4) HMRC annual returns (pension scheme return -- Pension Scheme Tax Reference -- PSTR), (5) HMRC QROPS (qualifying recognised overseas pension schemes -- transfer value for members leaving UK). HMRC API integration: ClickMasters automates HMRC RAS claim monthly and annual pension scheme return. TPR Scheme Return and Auto-Enrolment: The Pensions Regulator (TPR): (1) scheme return (annual TPR online return -- scheme membership, assets, governance), (2) auto-enrolment (TPR requires all employers to auto-enrol eligible workers -- pension platform must confirm auto-enrolment compliance), (3) DC Chair statement (annual chair statement published on pension website -- governance evidence), (4) value for members (VfM) assessment (TPR requires DC schemes to assess value for members annually -- cost and charges, investment performance, communications). ClickMasters TPR automation: scheme return data extracted from platform, auto-enrolment compliance confirmed monthly (HMRC PAYE data cross-check), VfM assessment data generated automatically.",
    "results": "PDP Connect ATLAS staging: passed. PDP live connection: confirmed. Platform live at 26 weeks, GBP122,000. 280,000 members. PDP Find request response: 99.8% within 5-second SLA. PDP Data request response: 99.6% within 10-second SLA. HMRC RAS claim: automated monthly (GBP4.2M tax relief claimed). TPR scheme return: automated. ISO 27001 maintained. Cyber Essentials Plus confirmed.",
