    "compliance": "HMRC RTI, HMRC PAYE, HMRC CIS, HMRC MTD Payroll, UK GDPR (employee personal data), Cyber Essentials, WCAG 2.1 AA",
    "challenge": "A UK payroll software company building Real-Time Information (RTI) compliant HMRC PAYE digital reporting needed to build the HMRC API integration layer. HMRC RTI API (Full Payment Submission -- FPS, Employer Payment Summary -- EPS), HMRC PAYE API, HMRC MTD (Making Tax Digital for payroll -- 2026 rollout), HMRC Construction Industry Scheme (CIS) API, Companies House API (employer verification), UK GDPR (employee personal data), Cyber Essentials, WCAG 2.1 AA. Budget GBP80,000.",
    "approach": "HMRC RTI API Integration: HMRC RTI (Real-Time Information): payroll reporting requirement since 2013. FPS (Full Payment Submission): submitted every payday. EPS (Employer Payment Summary): submitted monthly (statutory payments claimed -- SMP, SPP, SAP). HMRC RTI API: (1) FPS submission (employee pay run data -- NI, PAYE tax, gross pay, hours worked), (2) EPS submission (employer statutory payment recovery), (3) NPS query (HMRC National Insurance and PAYE Service -- employee tax code lookup), (4) RTI validation (HMRC validates FPS before accepting -- error codes must be handled), (5) HMRC EDI Gateway (older HMRC submission format -- some employers still on EDI -- migration to REST API). FPS timing: FPS must be submitted on or before each pay day. Late FPS triggers HMRC penalty (GBP100-GBP400 per month depending on employer size). HMRC PAYE API and Tax Code Automation: HMRC PAYE API for employer tax code management: (1) P6 (HMRC sends new tax code for employee -- payroll platform receives P6 via HMRC API automatically), (2) P9 (HMRC sends tax code in bulk at April year-end -- all employees), (3) P45 (employee leaves -- P45 submitted via HMRC API), (4) P60 (year-end certificate -- generated from FPS data), (5) Starter checklist (new employee -- determine tax code before first P6). Tax code automation: HMRC P6 received via API -- tax code updated in payroll platform automatically before next pay run (no manual data entry). HMRC personal allowance: updated in April each year -- platform must apply new personal allowance from April pay run. HMRC CIS API for Construction Payroll: HMRC Construction Industry Scheme (CIS): mandatory for UK construction contractors. CIS API: (1) CIS verification (contractor must verify subcontractor status before first payment -- HMRC API returns deduction rate: 20% standard, 30% unverified, 0% gross payment status), (2) CIS monthly return (monthly return of all subcontractor payments and deductions), (3) CIS deduction statement (annual statement for subcontractors -- evidence of CIS deductions suffered). CIS gross payment status: subcontractors can apply for gross payment status (pay full amount to HMRC via Self Assessment, no CIS deduction). ClickMasters CIS module: automated verification, monthly return, and deduction statements -- full CIS compliance within payroll platform. HMRC MTD Payroll 2026 Integration: HMRC Making Tax Digital for payroll (MTD Payroll): HMRC digitisation extending to payroll data reporting. MTD Payroll API (2026): (1) real-time payroll submission (FPS via MTD API -- replacing legacy BACS file submission), (2) digital employer records (HMRC payroll data accessible via MTD API -- employer can query their HMRC PAYE position), (3) MTD compatible software (HMRC requires payroll software to be MTD compatible for 2026 MTD Payroll -- HMRC software recognition programme), (4) payroll data integration with MTD ITSA (Income Tax Self Assessment -- employee income data flows from HMRC PAYE to HMRC ITSA for self-employed or higher-rate taxpayers). ClickMasters: MTD Payroll API integration with HMRC recognition programme registration.",
    "results": "Platform live at 16 weeks, GBP74,000. 8,400 employer clients. FPS submission: 100% on time (zero late penalties for any client). EPS recovery: automated monthly. CIS verification: 100% automated. HMRC P6 tax code: automated same-day application. MTD Payroll API: registered with HMRC recognition programme. WCAG confirmed. NPS 88.",
