    "id": "P1738",
    "slug": "nhs-digital-pharmacy-dispensing-platform-eps",
    "title": "NHS Digital Pharmacy Dispensing Platform -- EPS and NHS BSA",
    "metaTitle": "NHS Digital Pharmacy Dispensing Platform -- EPS and NHS BSA -- ClickMasters Case Study",
    "metaDesc": "A UK pharmacy chain (840 branches, 2.8M prescription items per month) needed to modernise their dispensing pla...",
    "sector": "",
    "country": "",
    "status": "",
    "contract": "",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "EPS (NHS Digital), NHS BSA, GPhC standards, CQC, Home Office CD Regulations, NHS DTAC all 5 domains, DCB0129, UK GDPR Article 9, Cyber Essentials Plus",
    "challenge": "A UK pharmacy chain (840 branches, 2.8M prescription items per month) needed to modernise their dispensing platform -- replacing a legacy Titan Pharmacy system with a cloud-native dispensing management system. EPS (Electronic Prescription Service -- NHS Digital), NHS BSA (Business Services Authority -- prescription pricing and payment), NCSO (No Cheaper Stock Obtainable -- drug pricing), NHS DTAC all 5 domains, DCB0129, GPhC (General Pharmaceutical Council -- pharmacy regulation), CQC (Care Quality Commission), UK GDPR Article 9 (prescription data is health data), GDS design principles for patient-facing elements. Budget GBP150,000.",
    "approach": "EPS (Electronic Prescription Service) Integration: EPS (Electronic Prescription Service): NHS Digital service allowing GPs to send prescriptions electronically to pharmacies. EPS integration: (1) EPS prescription download (pharmacy nominates a dispensing point -- prescriptions downloaded from NHS Spine via EPS API), (2) dispense claim (pharmacy dispenses prescription -- claim submitted to NHS BSA via EPS), (3) dispense notification (patient notification sent via EPS when prescription ready for collection), (4) prescription tracker (NHS App integration -- patient tracks prescription status), (5) cancellation handling (GP cancels prescription via EPS -- pharmacy must stop dispensing). NHS Spine connectivity: EPS requires NHS Spine connection (HSCN -- same as PDS, GP Connect). ClickMasters EPS: HSCN onboarding started day 1. NHS BSA Prescription Pricing: NHS BSA (Business Services Authority) prescription pricing and reimbursement: (1) FP10 claim (pharmacy submits monthly FP10 claim to NHS BSA -- all dispensed items), (2) Drug Tariff (NHS BSA publishes Drug Tariff monthly -- price paid for each drug), (3) NCSO (No Cheaper Stock Obtainable) -- when drug is out of stock, pharmacy claims NCSO reimbursement at higher rate), (4) endorsement (pharmacy must endorse prescription correctly -- endorsement errors cause NHS BSA payment reductions), (5) contractor payment (NHS BSA pays pharmacy monthly -- reimbursement + dispensing fee + service fees). Automated FP10 claim generation: ClickMasters platform auto-generates FP10 claim from dispensed items -- pharmacy pharmacist reviews and submits. GPhC and CQC Compliance in Dispensing System: GPhC (General Pharmaceutical Council): pharmacy professional regulator. GPhC standards for dispensing systems: (1) SOPs (Standard Operating Procedures) -- dispensing SOP must be documented and accessible in system), (2) CD register (Controlled Drugs register -- CD dispensing logged digitally -- Home Office CD regulations), (3) near miss log (dispensing near misses logged -- GPhC expects near miss analysis), (4) patient safety alert (MHRA and NHS BSA patient safety alerts -- system must show active alerts for affected drugs), (5) audit trail (every dispensing action logged -- GPhC inspection expects complete audit trail). ClickMasters GPhC module: SOPs displayed at point of dispense, CD register automated, near miss workflow, patient safety alert feed. Patient-Facing NHS App Integration: NHS App integration for pharmacy: (1) prescription tracking (patient sees prescription status on NHS App -- nominated pharmacy, dispensed, ready to collect), (2) repeat prescription ordering (patient orders repeat via NHS App -- EPS sends to pharmacy), (3) My Planned Care (NHS App -- planned care pathway -- pharmacy receives discharge prescription from hospital), (4) NHS Login (patient authenticates via NHS Login P9 -- accesses prescription history), (5) pharmacy search (NHS App pharmacy search -- pharmacy registers dispensing location on NHS App). ClickMasters pharmacy NHS App: prescription tracking real-time (patient sees dispensing status updated within 60 seconds of dispense action).",
    "results": "NHS DTAC all 5 domains approved. EPS live. Platform live at 28 weeks, GBP138,000. 840 branches. 2.8M prescription items/month. EPS download: 100% automated. FP10 claim: automated monthly. CD register: 100% digital. Near miss log: 94.2% compliance rate (was 68.4% paper). NHS App prescription tracking: 100% real-time. GPhC inspection: confirmed compliant. DCB0129 zero incidents.",
