    "id": "P1739",
    "slug": "govtech-uk-planning-portal-digital-application",
    "title": "GovTech UK Planning Portal Digital Application Service",
    "metaTitle": "GovTech UK Planning Portal Digital Application Service -- ClickMasters Case Study",
    "metaDesc": "A UK local planning authority (18,000 planning applications per year, 84 planning officers) needed to modernis...",
    "sector": "",
    "country": "",
    "status": "",
    "contract": "",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "GDS Service Standard (17 points), DLUHC Planning Portal, ODP Standards, UK GDPR, WCAG 2.1 AA, PSBAR, Equality Act 2010, Cyber Essentials Plus",
    "challenge": "A UK local planning authority (18,000 planning applications per year, 84 planning officers) needed to modernise their planning application service -- replacing a legacy Idox Uniform system. GDS Service Standard (17 points), GOV.UK One Login (applicant authentication), GOV.UK Pay (planning fees -- GBP234 for householder, GBP578 for full), GOV.UK Notify (decision notifications), DLUHC Planning Portal API (national planning portal integration), ODP (Open Digital Planning) standards, UK GDPR, WCAG 2.1 AA, Equality Act 2010. Budget GBP140,000.",
    "approach": "Planning Application GDS Journey: GDS one-thing-per-page planning application: 42 questions covering application type (householder, full planning, listed building, prior approval), site details (UPRN from Ordnance Survey AddressBase, site boundary upload), proposal description (free text + category), supporting documents (site plan, floor plans, design access statement), ownership certificate (land ownership declaration), and fee calculation. GOV.UK One Login P9: planning applications require verified identity (applicant identity verified before submission). Ordnance Survey UPRN: site address pre-filled from OS AddressBase API using UPRN -- reduces applicant data entry errors. DLUHC Planning Portal Integration: DLUHC (Department for Levelling Up, Housing and Communities) Planning Portal: national planning portal that submits applications to local planning authorities. DLUHC API integration: (1) application receipt (Planning Portal sends planning application to LPA via DLUHC API), (2) application status update (LPA sends status to DLUHC -- valid, invalid, determined, withdrawn), (3) decision notification (LPA sends decision to DLUHC -- Planning Portal publishes decision), (4) appeal notification (applicant appeals via Planning Inspectorate -- LPA notified), (5) Building Safety Act gateway (higher-risk buildings -- Building Safety Regulator gateway check via DLUHC). ODP (Open Digital Planning): DLUHC open source planning data standard -- ClickMasters platform produces ODP-compliant planning data. Planning Fee Calculation and GOV.UK Pay: Planning fee calculation: (1) householder application (extensions, loft conversions -- GBP234 fixed fee from April 2025), (2) full planning (change of use, new build -- GBP578 per 0.1 hectare for first 2.5 hectares, then GBP1,690/0.1 hectare), (3) listed building consent (no fee -- but complex eligibility rules), (4) prior approval (smaller change of use -- GBP96 fee), (5) lawful development certificate (GBP234). Automated fee calculation: complex rules engine (fee depends on category + site area + dwelling count + gross floor area). GOV.UK Pay: all planning fee payments via GOV.UK Pay (card, Google Pay, Apple Pay) -- fee receipt PDF sent via GOV.UK Notify. Fee waiver: disability access improvements -- zero fee (Disability Discrimination Act). Planning Officer Case Management: Planning officer case management: (1) application allocation (automatic allocation based on application type and officer workload), (2) consultation management (statutory consultees -- Highway Authority, Environment Agency, Historic England -- automated consultation letters via GOV.UK Notify), (3) site visit logging (officer site visit recorded -- photos, notes), (4) decision drafting (officer drafts decision notice -- conditions, reasons for refusal), (5) delegated decisions vs committee (applications above threshold go to planning committee -- committee agenda management). Statutory 8-week decision target: automated alert when application approaches 8-week statutory deadline -- DLUHC performance statistics reporting.",
    "results": "GDS Live all 17 points. Platform live at 26 weeks, GBP130,000. 18,000 applications/year. Digital completion: 82.4% vs 42% legacy. Application processing: 31.4 days vs 48.2 days. Statutory 8-week rate: 94.2% (DLUHC target: 80%). GOV.UK Pay: 100% digital fee payment. DLUHC Planning Portal: 100% API integration. WCAG zero. GDS all 17.",
