    "compliance": "UK GDPR (candidate personal data), ICO Registration, Cyber Essentials, PECR marketing consent",
    "challenge": "A UK recruitment technology startup needed to build a B2B SaaS platform for independent recruitment agencies — providing applicant tracking, client management, placement management, and commission calculation. The market was dominated by legacy desktop software (Bond Adapt, Bullhorn) with annual licences of £3,000–£12,000 per user. The founder had identified an opportunity to build a modern, web-based ATS at £80–£150/user/month. Pre-seed budget: £120,000 for MVP.",
    "approach": "Architecture: Next.js frontend, Node.js/Fastify backend, PostgreSQL separate schema per tenant (customer data isolation), Stripe for subscription billing (per-seat pricing), AWS eu-west-2. UK GDPR for Candidate Data: Recruitment platforms process sensitive personal data: candidate CVs, salary expectations, contact details, employment history. UK GDPR lawful basis: legitimate interest for processing candidate data shared directly; consent for marketing. Right to erasure: candidates can request deletion — implemented with soft-delete (anonymisation) to preserve placement history integrity. Microsoft 365 Integration: Recruitment agencies use Outlook and Teams heavily. ClickMasters built: Graph API integration for email sync (two-way), Teams webhook for placement notifications, SharePoint for document storage, and Azure AD SSO for enterprise client authentication. Multi-Tenancy: PostgreSQL separate schema per agency tenant. Row-Level Security as belt-and-braces isolation. Tenant-specific custom fields (agencies have different placement types and commission structures).",
    "results": "MVP launched at 14 weeks, £112,000 — under budget. 6 paying agency customers within 8 weeks of launch at £120/user/month. Average 8 users per agency. MRR at 3 months: £5,760. Series A conversation began at month 4 based on growth trajectory. Legacy software replacement displacement rate: 3 agencies cancelled Bond Adapt within 60 days.",
