    "approach": "IoT Architecture: MQTT protocol for vehicle-to-cloud telemetry (low-bandwidth vehicle connectivity). AWS IoT Core (eu-west-2) for message ingestion. Kinesis Data Streams for real-time telemetry processing. PostgreSQL for structured fleet data. TimescaleDB extension for time-series GPS data (1-second position updates for 320 vehicles = 27.6 million data points per day). DVSA Tachograph Integration: Automated tachograph data download requests via Continental VDO API. Infringement detection: EU Drivers Hours Regulations (Regulation (EC) No 561/2006 as retained in UK law). DVSA reporting: weekly infringement summary by driver and vehicle. UK GDPR for Driver Location Data: Legitimate interest basis documented (fleet management, drivers' hours compliance, road safety). Privacy Notice provided to all drivers at employment start. Right to access: driver portal enabling each driver to view their own historical location data. Data retention: 28 days raw GPS, 12 months tachograph data (DVSA minimum). Fuel Management Integration: CAN bus integration for fuel consumption data. Fuel card transaction API (Fleetcor UK). Fuel efficiency reporting by driver and route. CO2 emissions calculation for UK Streamlined Energy and Carbon Reporting (SECR).",
    "results": "Single platform deployed at 14 weeks, £88,000 — under budget. DVSA tachograph compliance: 100% of vehicles downloading within 28-day window (previously 62% compliant). Driver infringement rate: 18% reduction in first 3 months. Fuel efficiency: 4.2% improvement (driver behaviour coaching enabled by real-time data). UK GDPR audit: zero findings. Three drivers exercised right of access — all requests fulfilled within 24 hours (UK GDPR requires within 1 month).",
