    "approach": "Architecture: Next.js frontend (GOV.UK Design System as accessibility baseline), Node.js/Fastify backend, PostgreSQL per-student data with Row-Level Security, AWS eu-west-2, Azure AD SSO for Microsoft accounts. WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance: Legally required under PSBAR 2018 for public sector FE colleges. GOV.UK Design System components as baseline (WCAG 2.1 AA by design). Manual screen reader testing with NVDA and JAWS on every sprint. Colour contrast automated testing in CI/CD (Axe). Keyboard navigation tested by QA engineer for every UI component. Accessibility statement published on launch. ICO Children's Code Compliance: Students under 18 present. Privacy settings default to high. No behavioural analytics for under-18 students. Clear, plain-language privacy information designed for 16–17 year olds (Flesch reading ease above 60). Parental notification capability for students under 18. Data minimisation: only data genuinely needed for educational purposes collected. MIS and Teams Integration: Pearson Progressions MIS: student enrolment, attendance, and course assignment synced daily. Microsoft Graph API: Teams live class launch from LMS (single sign-on, class roster synchronisation), OneDrive integration for assignment submission, Teams notifications for grades.",
