    "approach": "Conveyancing Document Engine: Template-driven document generation: HMLR AP1 (application to register), TR1 (transfer of land), TP1 (transfer of part), DS1 (discharge of charge). SDLT calculation engine (all transaction types: freehold, leasehold, mixed use, additional dwelling). Completion statement automation with client-side balance checking. HMLR and HMRC API Integration: HMLR Digital Registration Service API for AP1 e-lodgement. HMRC SDLT API for electronic SDLT returns. HMLR Official Copies API for title register retrieval at instruction. Requisition response tracking via HMLR case management portal webhook. SRA Compliance Architecture: File audit trail: every document, every action, every user — timestamped and immutable. Conflict check workflow: matter opened triggers automated conflict search against all existing clients and related parties. Client money accounting: completion funds tracked separately from firm funds (SRA accounts rules). UK GDPR for Conveyancing Data: Conveyancing files contain substantial personal data: financial history (mortgage statements), identity documents, beneficial ownership information. Retention policy: SRA requires 6 years post-completion. UK GDPR minimisation: only data needed for conveyancing retained — no additional profiling. Right to access: DSAR response within 1 month.",
