    "compliance": "UK GDPR (driver data minimisation), Cyber Essentials, SAP data governance, Retail EDI standards (GS1)",
    "challenge": "A UK FMCG manufacturer producing 340 product SKUs across 4 factories needed real-time supply chain visibility — from raw material supplier through production to retail distribution centre delivery. Existing data sat in SAP (ERP), 3 separate WMS (Warehouse Management Systems), carrier tracking systems (DHL, Royal Mail, FedEx), and retailer EDI portals (Tesco, Sainsbury's, Asda). No single view of inventory position or order status existed. Budget: £140,000.",
    "approach": "Integration Architecture: Data orchestration via Apache Airflow (workflow orchestration). SAP integration via RFC (Remote Function Calls) for production orders and material movements. REST API integration for WMS systems (2 custom-built, 1 Infor WMS). DHL, Royal Mail, FedEx tracking APIs. Retailer EDI: AS2/EDIFACT parsing for Tesco/Sainsbury's/Asda purchase orders and delivery confirmations. Real-Time Inventory Engine: PostgreSQL TimescaleDB for time-series inventory positions (all SKUs across all locations, 1-hour snapshots). Redis for current inventory cache (sub-10ms read latency for dashboard). Inventory calculation: SAP stock positions + WMS adjustments + in-transit stock (from carrier tracking) + retailer confirmed deliveries. UK GDPR and Data Governance: Supply chain data: primarily business data (not personal). Exception: driver delivery data (name, van registration) as personal data. UK GDPR basis: legitimate interest for delivery management. Driver data minimised: name/registration retained for 30 days only. Supplier contact data: Article 28 DPA with data integration service providers. Retail Compliance Monitoring: Tesco and Sainsbury's On-Time In-Full (OTIF) monitoring: automated alerts when delivery is at risk of missing retailer OTIF windows. OTIF penalties (common in UK retail) can be significant — real-time visibility enables proactive intervention. Buyer portal: retailers access their own delivery tracking (tenant isolation via read-only API token).",
    "results": "Platform live at 18 weeks, £132,000 — under budget. Inventory position accuracy: 94% → 99.7% (real-time vs end-of-day batch). OTIF performance: improved from 87% → 96% (Tesco target is 95%). Estimated OTIF penalty reduction: £180,000 per year. Out-of-stock events at retail: reduced 34%. Management decision time for supply issues: from 2 days (when someone noticed) to 2 hours (automated alert).",
