    "compliance": "ICO AADC (Children's Code), UK GDPR (under-18 users), PECR, WCAG 2.1 AA, Cyber Essentials",
    "challenge": "A UK EdTech startup wanted to build an adaptive learning platform for GCSE revision — serving Year 10 and Year 11 students. ICO AADC compliance (all users under 18), dual B2C (direct student subscription) and B2B (school licence) channels, and adaptive question difficulty algorithm. Budget: £80,000.",
    "approach": "ICO AADC Compliance: Privacy by default: high privacy settings as default for all users. No behavioural advertising. No nudge techniques to encourage over-sharing. Age gate: under-13 users require parental consent (email verification of parent). 13–17: student's own consent valid but must be in plain language. No social features (messaging, competitive leaderboards showing personal names) without explicit opt-in. Adaptive Algorithm: Spaced repetition (SM-2 algorithm) + dynamic difficulty adjustment: question difficulty increases when a student answers 3 consecutive questions correctly, decreases after 2 consecutive incorrect. Knowledge graph: 8 GCSE subjects × 400+ topic nodes, each with prerequisite relationships. Mastery score per topic drives spaced repetition scheduling. Dual B2C/B2B Architecture: B2C: Stripe subscription (£5.99/month individual). B2B: school licence with class management dashboard, teacher progress view (not individual student performance — privacy protection), bulk student import via CSV. School admin portal: SIMS-compatible CSV format for bulk onboarding. Offline Learning (PWA): Progressive Web App: Service Worker caches question bank per subject for offline revision. Offline answers queued and synced on reconnect. UK GDPR: Service Worker cache cleared on logout, progress data never cached unencrypted.",
    "results": "Launched at 12 weeks, £76,000 — under budget. 4,200 students in first 6 months (2,800 B2C, 1,400 via 12 school B2B licences). ICO AADC audit: zero findings. Revision session length: 23 minutes average (industry benchmark for effective revision: 20–30 minutes). Student retention at 30 days: 64% (industry benchmark: 45%). Series A conversation at month 7.",
