    "compliance": "HSE Offshore Safety, Environment Agency CfD reporting, UK GDPR (employee/contractor data), Marine Management Organisation (MMO) marine licence, Cyber Essentials",
    "challenge": "A UK offshore wind operator managing 48 turbines needed to replace 3 separate monitoring systems (SCADA data, maintenance records, and environmental reporting) with a single platform. UK GDPR for employee and contractor data, Environment Agency reporting requirements, and HSE offshore safety obligations were the compliance requirements. Real-time turbine performance analytics, predictive maintenance alerts, and carbon performance reporting (for CfD contract obligations) were the business requirements. Budget: £110,000.",
    "approach": "SCADA Data Integration: OPC-UA protocol bridge: SCADA systems use OPC-UA (industrial standard) — ClickMasters built a Node.js OPC-UA client polling turbine metrics (output power, wind speed, rotor RPM, gearbox temperature, pitch angle) at 1-minute intervals. AWS IoT Core for cloud ingestion, TimescaleDB for time-series storage (1.2M data points per day for 48 turbines). Predictive Maintenance ML: Python scikit-learn anomaly detection: gearbox temperature deviation from baseline (turbine-specific models — each gearbox has different baseline characteristics), bearing vibration pattern analysis, and power curve deviation (actual output vs theoretical output at measured wind speed). Alert threshold: 2.5 standard deviations from 30-day rolling baseline triggers maintenance recommendation. Environment Agency Reporting: CfD (Contract for Difference) carbon reporting: automated monthly carbon output calculation per turbine (kWh × grid emissions factor), aggregated annual report in Environment Agency prescribed format. Marine licence compliance: vessel movement logs automatically populated from AIS data (automatic identification system) for maintenance vessel tracking in protected marine area. HSE Offshore Safety Compliance: Permit to Work (PTW) digital system: offshore maintenance jobs require PTW issuance, isolation confirmation, and sign-off before work commences. PTW audit trail satisfies HSE offshore safety obligations. Contractor competency tracking: offshore workers must have valid BOSIET (Basic Offshore Safety Induction), GWO (Global Wind Organisation), and medical certificates — all tracked with expiry alerts.",
    "results": "Platform live at 16 weeks, £103,000 — under budget. Predictive maintenance alerts: 4 gearbox anomalies detected 3–6 weeks before failure (estimated cost saving: £1.2M avoided repair costs). CfD reporting: Environment Agency commended automated reporting system in compliance audit. HSE inspection: PTW system praised as best practice for offshore maintenance safety. Turbine availability improvement: 98.2% → 99.1% (predictive maintenance reduces unplanned downtime).",
