    "compliance": "UK GDPR (member professional data), WCAG 2.1 AA (PSBAR 2018), Cyber Essentials, ICO registration",
    "challenge": "A UK professional institution with 45,000 members needed to replace their legacy membership management system (a 2004 CRM, heavily customised Salesforce, and a separate exam booking system). Members needed self-service account management, CPD (Continuing Professional Development) tracking, examination booking, and a public Professional Register. UK GDPR for member professional data, WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility (public sector PSBAR obligations for chartered institutions), and Stripe billing for subscription renewal were the requirements. Budget: £130,000.",
    "approach": "Member Self-Service Portal: Next.js member portal with Azure AD B2C (external identity) for secure member authentication. Self-service: profile management, subscription renewal (Stripe), CPD log entry, examination booking, and certificate download. Member dashboard: CPD target vs actual (institution requires 30 CPD hours/year), subscription status, and Professional Register listing management. CPD Tracking Engine: CPD log: members record activities (conference attendance, course completion, self-directed learning, mentoring). Verifiable CPD (CREST-certified training, etc.) vs self-declared CPD. Annual CPD cycle: auto-reset on membership renewal date. Institution can audit member CPD logs — audit workflow built in. CPD non-compliance alert: automated 90-day pre-renewal email if CPD target not met. Professional Register (Public-Facing): Publicly searchable register of chartered members. UK GDPR: members consent to public listing as part of chartered membership application. Right to erasure: removal from public register within 24 hours of cessation of membership. Search: name, company, specialism, region. Verification API: employers can verify membership status via API (used by hiring companies). Examination Booking and Results: Examination booking: 6 exam sittings per year, online and centre-based. Integration with examination centre booking API. Results posting: automated member notification on result publication. Certificate generation: PDF certificate with member name, exam, date, and institution digital signature. Historic examination records: members can view all past results.",
    "results": "Platform live at 18 weeks, £124,000 — under budget. Legacy Salesforce licence saving: £85,000/year (ROI payback year 1). Member self-service adoption: 92% of renewals now online (was 41%). CPD compliance rate: 71% → 89% (automated reminders). Professional Register API: 28 companies integrated for candidate verification. WCAG 2.1 AA: Cabinet Office monitoring — zero non-compliances. Staff admin time per renewal: 22 minutes → 4 minutes.",
