    "challenge": "A UK personal injury law firm processing 8,400 cases per year needed to replace their legacy case management system (Proclaim, heavily customised over 15 years). CFA (Conditional Fee Agreement) management, disbursement tracking, Clio integration, MOJ Portal for RTA claims, and MedCo panel management were all required. SRA accounts rules compliance, Legal Professional Privilege architecture, AML obligations, and UK GDPR for sensitive injury and medical data were the compliance requirements. Budget: £140,000.",
    "approach": "CFA Financial Architecture: CFA management: success fee calculation per case type and complexity band, ATE (After The Event insurance) premium tracking, disbursement ledger per case (medical reports, court fees, expert fees), bill of costs generation in standard SCCO (Senior Courts Costs Office) format, and profit cost calculation. CFA outcomes: settled, won at trial, lost — each triggers different financial calculation. MOJ RTA Portal Integration: Ministry of Justice RTA Claims Portal API for Stage 1 and Stage 2 road traffic accident claims. Automated CNF (Claim Notification Form) submission. Stage 2 settlement negotiation tracking. Portal response tracking with SLA alerts (defendant must respond within 15 business days at Stage 1). Automatic progression trigger: no response within SLA → Stage 3 court process initiated. SRA Accounts Rules Compliance: Client ledger per case: client money completely isolated from office money (SRA Accounts Rules 2.1). Disbursement payments: immediate notation on client ledger. Bills delivered: transfer from client account to office account only after bill delivery. Monthly reconciliation automation: client account bank statement reconciliation against client ledger. SRA audit trail: every client account transaction immutable and attributed. MedCo and Medical Evidence Management: MedCo panel medico-legal report management: MedCo report request (via MedCo API), report receipt and quality review workflow, claimant appointment confirmation, and report storage with UK GDPR medical data controls. Medical evidence qualifies as special category data (UK GDPR Article 9) — access restricted to fee earners on the specific case.",
    "results": "Platform live at 16 weeks, £132,000 — under budget. Bill of costs generation: 3.5 days manual → 45 minutes automated. MOJ Portal response rate within SLA: 94% (previously untracked — estimated 78%). CFA profit costs per case: 18% improvement (better disbursement tracking reduced write-offs). SRA accounts audit: zero findings. AML: 100% of new client CDD completed at file open (was 67%).",
