    "metaDesc": "A Magic Circle law firm conducting a major M&amp;A due diligence transaction needed to review 840,000 documents (f...",
    "sector": "LegalTech / AI",
    "country": "UK",
    "status": "On Time",
    "contract": "Fixed Price",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "Legal Professional Privilege (LPP), UK GDPR (third-party corporate data), SRA Code of Conduct, Cyber Essentials, on-premises (no external data transfer)",
    "challenge": "A Magic Circle law firm conducting a major M&amp;A due diligence transaction needed to review 840,000 documents (financial records, contracts, regulatory filings) in a 6-week data room review period. Traditional review at the firm's standard rate would require 28,000 fee earner hours — commercially and practically impossible. Legal Professional Privilege architecture, UK GDPR data processing for third-party company data, and SRA professional obligations for AI-assisted review were the constraints. Budget: £85,000 (technology component only — fee earner review of AI outputs billed separately).",
    "approach": "On-Premises RAG Architecture: LPP constraint: 840,000 documents cannot be sent to any external AI API. ClickMasters deployed on-premises: Llama 3.1 70B (4-bit quantised, running on firm's A100 GPU cluster), LangChain RAG pipeline, Chroma vector store (local). Document ingestion pipeline: PDF extraction (PyMuPDF), chunking (512 tokens), embedding (local Nomic Embed Text model), and storage in Chroma. Zero document data leaves the firm's network. Due Diligence Classification: Classification taxonomy: 12 document categories (Material Contract, Regulatory Correspondence, Financial Statement, IP Assignment, Employment Contract, Dispute/Litigation, Real Property, Permits, Insurance, Corporate Governance, Tax, Other). ML classifier (scikit-learn, fine-tuned on 2,000 manually-labelled due diligence documents): first-pass classification at ingestion. Confidence threshold: documents below 80% confidence flagged for senior associate review. Privilege Screening: Privilege screening: dedicated LLM query per document checking for indicators of legal professional privilege (law firm names, \"privileged and confidential\" headers, legal advice language). Privilege candidates: flagged for privilege review before any further processing. SRA professional obligation: privilege screening is the first step — privileged documents are quarantined and reviewed manually before inclusion in data room analysis. Review Workflow and Audit Trail: Associate review interface: classified documents presented with AI summary, classification confidence, and key extracted terms. One-click accept/reclassify/escalate. SRA audit trail: every document, every classification decision, every reclassification, every reviewer — immutable log. Partner sign-off dashboard: review progress, classification distribution, and risk concentration heatmap per deal category.",
    "results": "Deployed at 3 weeks (compressed timeline for transaction), £78,000 — under budget. Documents classified: 840,000 in 96 hours. First-pass classification accuracy (validated against 2,000 sample): 94.7%. Review time for associate team: 6 weeks × 8 associates (384 fee earner hours) vs estimated 28,000 hours without AI (98.6% reduction). LPP: zero privileged documents included in data room output without manual review. SRA audit trail: commended in subsequent Law Society AI guidance review.",
