    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "DVSA Operator's Licence compliance, tachograph regulations, UK GDPR (driver data), Cyber Essentials",
    "challenge": "A UK third-party logistics (3PL) operator running 340 HGVs and 12 distribution centres needed to replace four separate systems: a legacy TMS (Transport Management System from 2011), a GPS tracking system (no integration with TMS), a manual POD (Proof of Delivery) process, and spreadsheet-based SLA reporting. Operator's Licence compliance (DVSA, tachograph data), UK GDPR for driver data, and real-time customer visibility portal were the requirements. Budget: £140,000.",
    "approach": "Real-Time Vehicle Telematics Integration: Samsara fleet telematics API: real-time vehicle position (30-second interval), tachograph data (driving time, rest periods, infringement events), vehicle diagnostics (fault codes, fuel consumption), and HOS (Hours of Service) compliance monitoring. DVSA compliance: automated tachograph analysis generating weekly compliance reports. Infringement alerts: driver-specific real-time alerts for HOS violations before they become DVSA reportable offences. TMS Route Optimisation: Google Maps Platform Routes API with HGV-specific constraints: height restrictions, weight limits, road type exclusions. Multi-stop route optimisation: 50+ delivery stops per route, time-window constraints per customer, vehicle capacity constraints. Dynamic re-routing: real-time traffic integration — route updates pushed to driver cab via in-cab unit. Estimated Time of Arrival (ETA): ML model trained on historical route completion data improves accuracy vs Google Maps default. Digital POD and Customer Portal: React Native driver app: digital POD (photo, signature, barcode scan), delivery exception reporting (damaged goods, access issues, customer not available), and real-time communication with depot. Customer visibility portal: real-time consignment tracking, ETA notifications (GOV.UK Notify equivalent — email/SMS), and POD document download. Customer API: webhook for consignment status events for customers with WMS integration. DVSA and Operator Licence Compliance: Operator's Licence: vehicle maintenance schedules (MOT, safety inspection intervals) tracked and alerted. Tachograph analysis: automated infringement detection and DVSA-format compliance reports. Vehicle daily walk-around check: digital checklist replacing paper — defects reported to workshop management system. Drivers' hours dashboard: real-time HOS status per driver, weekly/fortnightly driving time summaries.",
    "results": "Platform live at 18 weeks, £132,000 — under budget. Route efficiency: 8.4% fewer vehicle-miles (fuel saving + carbon reduction). On-time delivery performance: 87% → 96%. Customer portal adoption: 89% of customers using portal for tracking (reducing customer service calls 62%). DVSA compliance: tachograph infringement rate reduced 71%. POD dispute resolution: average 3.2 days → same-day (digital POD eliminates paper chase).",
