    "status": "On Time",
    "contract": "Fixed Price",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "SRA Code of Conduct, SRA Accounts Rules, UK GDPR (patent applicant and attorney data), Cyber Essentials, EPO epi Guidelines",
    "challenge": "A UK patent attorney firm managing 4,800 active patent and trademark cases across 60 jurisdictions needed to replace their legacy Inprotech (IP management software, 2009 version) with a modern platform. EPO (European Patent Office) and UKIPO API integration for patent status and deadline tracking, WIPO Madrid System for trademark management, AnnuitiesPayment (IPRenewal) for automated renewal payment, and SRA-compliant matter management were mandatory. Budget: £120,000.",
    "approach": "EPO OPS API Integration: European Patent Office Open Patent Services (OPS) API: patent bibliographic data, legal status (grant, refusal, withdrawal, lapse), family data (all patent family members across jurisdictions), and citation data. EP Register API: prosecution history (actions and communications per case). UKIPO API: UK patent grant data, renewal status, and legal status events. Automated case docketing: EPO official actions trigger automatic deadline calculation (response due dates per EPC Rules). Deadline Management Engine: IP deadline engine: jurisdiction-specific deadline calculation rules (EPO Rule 126 response periods, PCT national phase deadlines, trademark renewal windows). Paris Convention priority claiming deadlines. PCT 30-month national phase deadlines. Trademark Madrid Protocol designation deadlines. Alert cascade: 6 months, 3 months, 1 month, 2 weeks — each with email and in-app notification. Partner override: escalation if attorney does not acknowledge the 1-month alert. Automated Renewal Payments: AnnuitiesPayment / Dennemeyer integration for automated patent annuity payments. Renewal payment instructions generated from case records (EPO annuity due dates, UKIPO renewal dates). Approval workflow: attorney reviews and approves renewal instructions before payment submission. Payment confirmation: receipt stored against case record. Failed payment: immediate alert and manual escalation. WIPO Madrid Trademark System: WIPO Madrid Monitor API: trademark registration status across 130 member countries. Trademark renewal tracking: 10-year term plus 6-month grace period. Trademark watch service: WIPO Global Brand Database API for similar mark monitoring (early warning of potential conflicts). UK TM database integration post-Brexit: UKIPO trademark API (separate from EU trademark registry post-Brexit).",
    "results": "Platform live at 20 weeks, £112,000 — under budget. Zero missed deadlines in first 12 months of operation (legacy system: 3 missed deadlines in prior 12 months — each requiring UKIPO/EPO extension, which is costly and embarrassing). Annuity payment accuracy: 100% (no failed payments). Case status visibility: attorneys access real-time EPO prosecution status vs weekly manual EPOLINE checks. SRA accounts audit: zero findings.",
