    "title": "InsurTech Motor Fleet Telematics Platform — UK Commercial Insurer",
    "metaTitle": "InsurTech Motor Fleet Telematics Platform — UK Commercial Insurer — ClickMasters Case Study",
    "metaDesc": "A UK FCA-authorised commercial motor insurer with 4,200 fleet policies needed to build a telematics-based flee...",
    "sector": "InsurTech / Motor Fleet",
    "country": "UK",
    "status": "On Time",
    "contract": "Fixed Price",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "FCA ICOBS, FCA Consumer Duty, UK GDPR (employee monitoring), ICO employment practices, ABI MID, Cyber Essentials",
    "challenge": "A UK FCA-authorised commercial motor insurer with 4,200 fleet policies needed to build a telematics-based fleet risk platform — providing real-time driving behaviour scoring, dynamic premium adjustment, and fleet manager dashboards. FCA ICOBS (usage-based insurance disclosure requirements), UK GDPR for vehicle location and driver behaviour data (special category implications for employee monitoring), and MID (Motor Insurance Database) integration were the requirements. Budget: £110,000.",
    "approach": "Telematics Device Integration and Data Pipeline: OBD-II telematics devices (Geotab, Samsara, Lytx): CAN-bus vehicle data stream via device cloud API. Data points per trip: GPS coordinates (1-second intervals), speed, acceleration/braking g-force, cornering g-force, engine RPM, idling time, and driver ID (if fleet card integration active). Data pipeline: device cloud webhook → SQS → Lambda → PostgreSQL (TimescaleDB extension for time-series). Batch processing: daily trip scoring computed overnight. Driving Behaviour Scoring Model: Composite risk score (0–100 per trip): weighted algorithm: harsh braking events (25%), harsh acceleration (15%), speeding violations (30%), cornering (15%), night driving proportion (10%), trip distance (5%). Fleet score: 90-day rolling average. Score validation: back-tested against claims data — high-risk scores correlate with claims at 3.4x rate of low-risk scores. FCA ICOBS: scoring methodology disclosed in plain English to fleet manager. Dynamic Premium Adjustment: FCA ICOBS usage-based insurance: premium adjustment based on telematics must be disclosed at policy inception. Premium calculation: base premium × telematics adjustment factor (0.75–1.40). Quarterly review: score-based premium adjustment applied quarterly with 30-day notice. Adverse adjustment protection: FCA Consumer Duty — premium increase &gt; 15% triggers mandatory fleet manager contact before application. MID update: any policy change triggers MID update via ABI/DVLA MID submission. UK GDPR Employee Monitoring Architecture: Employee telematics data is personal data. Legal basis: legitimate interests (road safety, vehicle security) with DPIA. ICO employment practices guidance: employees must be informed about telematics monitoring (privacy notice), data minimisation (location data retained for 90 days, trip summary retained for 7 years), and purpose limitation (not used for HR performance management — only insurance risk). Driver data separation: insurer sees fleet-level aggregated data; fleet manager sees driver scores but not individual trip locations.",
    "results": "Platform live at 16 weeks, £102,000 — under budget. Fleet risk score adoption: 3,400 of 4,200 policies telematic by end of year 1. Claims frequency (telematics fleet): 28% lower than non-telematics equivalent portfolios. Average premium reduction for good-score fleets: 12% (competitive advantage vs market). FCA ICOBS audit: usage-based insurance disclosure reviewed and confirmed compliant. ICO employee monitoring audit: data minimisation and purpose limitation confirmed compliant.",
    "clientQuote": "",
    "technologies": [],
