    "compliance": "FCA SM&amp;CR, FCA Consumer Duty (PS22/9), UK GDPR (compliance officer processing), Cyber Essentials",
    "challenge": "A UK FCA-authorised compliance consultancy providing outsourced compliance services to 85 FCA-regulated firms (IFAs, wealth managers, and insurance intermediaries) needed to build a RegTech compliance monitoring platform — replacing manual email-based compliance monitoring with automated FCA rule monitoring, incident tracking, and Board reporting. FCA SM&amp;CR (Senior Managers and Certification Regime), SMCR individual conduct rule monitoring, Consumer Duty outcome monitoring, and ICO registration status were the requirements. Budget: £90,000.",
    "approach": "FCA Register Live Monitoring: FCA Register API: automated daily check on each client firm's FCA registration status, permissions, and approved individual status. SM&amp;CR individual monitoring: approved persons list per firm cross-referenced against FCA Register — automatic alert if approved individual status changes (withdrawn, cancelled, prohibited). Regulatory news feed: FCA Enforcement notices, Dear CEO letters, and FCA Primary Market Bulletins automatically ingested and relevance-tagged per client firm. Consumer Duty Outcome Monitoring Framework: FCA Consumer Duty (PS22/9): firms must monitor outcomes across all four outcomes (Products and Services, Price and Value, Consumer Understanding, Consumer Support). Platform provides: outcome monitoring dashboards with firm-level RAG status, complaint analysis (categorised by Consumer Duty outcome), customer research scheduling (annual consumer testing requirement), and fair value assessment workflow (price and value outcome documentation). SM&amp;CR Certification and Training Tracking: SM&amp;CR Certification Regime: solo-regulated firms must certify individuals annually. Platform: individual certification due-date tracking, certification assessment workflow (competency evidence upload), annual renewal reminder cascade (90 days, 30 days, 7 days), and Training Year record (annual FCA conduct rules training completion per individual). Conduct Rule breach: incident recording, root cause analysis, and self-reporting to FCA workflow. Board Reporting Automation: Monthly compliance report for each client firm: automated from monitoring data. FCA-standard structure: regulatory change summary, breach/incident log, SM&amp;CR status, Consumer Duty outcome RAG, and upcoming regulatory milestones. PDF report generated automatically. Board distribution: email delivery to registered Board members. Audit trail: every report version retained with delivery confirmation.",
    "results": "Platform live at 14 weeks, £82,000 — under budget. FCA Register monitoring: 85 firms monitored daily (previously weekly manual check). FCA status changes detected: 6 in first 6 months — all flagged before client became aware. Consumer Duty outcome monitoring: 100% of client firms with documented monitoring frameworks (previously 34%). SM&amp;CR certification: 98% on-time completion rate (previously 78%). Board report generation: 3 hours per firm per month → 15 minutes automated.",
