    "compliance": "FCA credit broker authorisation, CCA credit brokerage disclosure, PSD2 payment accounts, UK GDPR, KYB/AML (MLRs 2017), Cyber Essentials",
    "challenge": "A UK B2B SaaS company providing project management software to 8,400 professional services firms wanted to embed financial products — invoice financing (receivables-based lending) and business bank accounts — directly into their platform. FCA authorisation as a credit broker and payment institution, Banking-as-a-Service (BaaS) provider integration (Modulr for accounts, Funding Circle for lending), UK GDPR, Consumer Credit Act (CCA) for credit brokerage, and PSD2 for payment accounts were the requirements. Budget: £130,000.",
    "approach": "FCA Authorisation Architecture: FCA credit broker (arranging credit — Article 36H RAO): client SaaS company applied for FCA authorisation. ClickMasters documented the technology architecture for the FCA regulatory business plan. Payment institution (PI) — e-money issuer via Modulr: utilising Modulr's FCA authorisation under the Modulr agency agreement (no separate PI authorisation required). FCA application technical annex: system architecture, data flows, controls, and UK GDPR compliance documentation. Modulr BaaS Integration: Modulr API: business account creation (e-money account per customer firm), sort code and account number assignment (UK-sort-coded accounts), inbound Faster Payments, outbound Faster Payments, Direct Debit origination, and account balance/transaction history. Account creation webhook: triggered when B2B SaaS customer activates the embedded finance feature. KYB (Know Your Business) — Companies House + Experian Commercial verification — automated at account creation. Funding Circle Embedded Lending: Funding Circle API: pre-qualification (soft credit check — no impact on credit file), loan application (term loan, invoice financing), credit decision, and loan offer. Invoice financing integration: purchase order and invoice data from the B2B SaaS project management system automatically populates the Funding Circle application. CCA credit brokerage disclosure: FCA-required pre-contract information presented in the B2B SaaS UI before credit application — FCA-approved disclosure text. Embedded Finance UK GDPR Architecture: Multi-party data processing: B2B SaaS company (controller), Modulr (processor for payment accounts), Funding Circle (independent controller for lending). Data sharing agreement: B2B SaaS company shares KYB data with Modulr and Funding Circle under Article 26 (joint controller) arrangements where applicable. Customer transparency: embedded finance privacy notice explains which data goes to which provider and on what legal basis.",
    "results": "Platform live at 18 weeks, £122,000 — under budget. FCA credit broker authorisation obtained. Embedded business accounts activated: 2,800 of 8,400 customers in first 6 months. Embedded lending (Funding Circle): 340 applications in first 6 months, average loan £42,000. B2B SaaS ARR uplift (embedded finance add-on fee): £840,000 additional annual revenue. FCA technical annex: accepted without revision on first submission.",
