    "contract": "Fixed Price",
    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "DTAC all 5 domains, DCB0129, HL7 v2 / FHIR R4 UK Core, NHS SDS, UK GDPR Article 9, NHS DSP Toolkit, WCAG 2.1 AA, Cyber Essentials Plus",
    "challenge": "An NHS Integrated Care System managing pathology results for 14 GP practices and 2 community hospitals needed to replace the legacy CITO (legacy pathology results viewer, 2008) with a modern pathology results platform — providing clinicians with real-time results, critical value alerting, and trend analysis. HL7 v2 to FHIR R4 migration, NHS Spine integration (SDS for authentication), DTAC all 5 domains, DCB0129 (critical value alerting is a patient safety priority), and UK GDPR Article 9 were the requirements. Budget: £75,000.",
    "approach": "FHIR R4 Pathology Results Integration: NHS Pathology FHIR R4 Implementation Guide: DiagnosticReport resource (report header — requesting clinician, specimen, report status), Observation resources (individual test results — LOINC codes, numeric values, reference ranges, abnormal flags). HL7 v2 ORU R01 → FHIR R4 transformation: HAPI FHIR message parser with UK Core profile validation. Bidirectional: receive results (HL7 v2 in, FHIR R4 out for viewer) and send orders (FHIR R4 ServiceRequest out). Critical Value Alerting: Critical values (results outside limits requiring urgent clinical action — e.g., potassium &gt; 6.0 mmol/L, haemoglobin &lt; 70 g/L, INR &gt; 10): automatic alert to requesting clinician within 5 minutes of result receipt. Alert channel: GOV.UK Notify SMS to clinician mobile + in-app notification. Acknowledgement required: clinician must acknowledge critical alert within 30 minutes — escalation to duty clinician if no acknowledgement. DCB0129 hazard: alert not delivered or acknowledged — mitigated by dual-channel plus escalation. NHS SDS Authentication: NHS Spine Directory Service (SDS): GP clinical system authentication for NHS Spine access. Smartcard integration: NHS Spine requires Smartcard (RA01/02) authentication for clinical data access. RBAC: NHS Spine Role Based Access Control — GP sees only results for their registered patients (ODS code matching). Audit: every result access logged with clinician NHS number and ODS code — NHS DSP Toolkit audit trail requirement. UK GDPR Article 9 Pathology Data: Pathology results: health data, Article 9 special category. Basis: Article 9(2)(h) — provision of health care. Retention: pathology results retained for 8 years (NHS Records Management Code — adults). Minimum necessary access: clinicians see only results for their registered patients. Results search: clinician cannot search by diagnosis or result value across population — only patient-level access.",
    "results": "DTAC approved all 5 domains. Platform live at 14 weeks, £68,000 — under budget. Critical value alert delivery: 100% within 5 minutes. Acknowledgement compliance: 94% within 30 minutes (target: 90%). Clinical result retrieval time: CITO average 4.1 minutes → new platform 18 seconds. Abnormal result trend analysis: 340 cases where trend identified before individual result crossed critical threshold. WCAG 2.1 AA: zero non-compliances.",
    "clientQuote": "",
    "technologies": [],
