    "technology": "",
    "compliance": "HMRC CIS, UK VAT, HMRC MTD (via Xero), UK GDPR, Consumer Credit Act (credit accounts), Cyber Essentials",
    "challenge": "A UK industrial supplies distributor with 3,400 B2B customers and 84,000 SKUs wanted to build a B2B marketplace platform — moving from a telephone and email order process to a self-service digital platform. Customer-specific pricing (negotiated trade accounts), credit account management, purchase order workflows, multiple buyers per account, VAT invoicing, and CIS (Construction Industry Scheme) compliance for construction customers were the requirements. Budget: £120,000.",
    "approach": "B2B Pricing Engine: Customer-specific pricing: 3,400 accounts × 84,000 SKUs = potential 285 million price points. Architecture: pricing rules engine rather than stored price matrix. Rules: customer tier (platinum/gold/silver/bronze), product category discount, quantity break pricing, and promotional overrides. Cache: Redis product catalogue with customer-specific price decoration per session (computed on-demand, cached 60 minutes). Price display: authenticated customer sees their negotiated price — unauthenticated visitors see RRP. Credit Account and Purchase Order Workflow: Credit accounts: £5,000–£500,000 credit limits per account (set by sales team). PO workflow: buyer submits order with PO number → credit check (available credit vs order value) → auto-approve or refer to credit controller → invoice generated on despatch. Multi-buyer accounts: multiple users per account with different permissions (buyer, approver, viewer). Approval workflow: orders above £5,000 require account admin approval before processing. CIS Construction Industry Scheme: HMRC CIS: construction industry customers are CIS contractors — they must have materials purchases separated from labour for CIS reporting. B2B marketplace CIS feature: customer flags account as CIS, VAT invoice separates materials and delivery charges, CIS monthly return data export (CSV in HMRC CIS return format). HMRC CIS verification: supplier verifies subcontractor registration status via HMRC CIS API before first payment. B2B VAT Invoice and Accounts Integration: VAT invoice requirements: customer VAT number, supplier VAT number, invoice number (sequential), VAT breakdown by rate (0%, 5%, 20%), supply date. Xero integration: invoices automatically synced to Xero (Xero API) on despatch — no double-entry. Customer VAT validation: HMRC Check a UK VAT Number API — verify customer VAT registration at account creation. Making Tax Digital: Xero handles MTD VAT return submission from synced invoice data.",
    "results": "Platform live at 18 weeks, £112,000 — under budget. Digital order rate: 0% → 68% in first 6 months. Phone/email order processing time: 4.2 hours/day → 1.1 hours (68% reduction). Credit account approval: 94% auto-approved within 2 seconds. Average order value (digital): 23% higher than phone orders (customer browses more products). CIS compliance: automated CIS monthly return data for 340 construction customers. HMRC VAT invoice audit: zero findings.",
    "clientQuote": "",
    "technologies": [],
    "complianceAchieved": "",
