    "challenge": "A UK FCA-authorised equity crowdfunding platform wanted to rebuild their legacy platform (2013 codebase, jQuery, no mobile experience) with a modern React/TypeScript architecture. FCA COBS 14 (appropriateness assessment for retail investors in non-readily realisable securities), FCA COBS 4 (financial promotions), FCA Consumer Duty PS22/9, UK GDPR for investor personal data, and Companies House API for company verification were the requirements. Budget: £120,000.",
    "approach": "FCA Appropriateness Assessment: COBS 14.3A.8: retail investors in non-readily realisable securities (unlisted equity) must pass an appropriateness assessment. Assessment engine: 8-question knowledge test (understanding of investment risk, illiquidity, dilution, EIS/SEIS tax reliefs). Scoring: pass (7/8 correct) → full access, refer (5–6/8) → additional risk warning + cooling-off, fail (&lt; 5/8) → cannot invest (exception: sophisticated investor self-certification or high net worth declaration). Elective professional investor: separate declaration process. FCA Financial Promotions Architecture: COBS 4: all financial promotions must be fair, clear, and not misleading. Crowdfunding pitches are financial promotions. Promotion approval workflow: company pitch → ClickMasters FCA compliance review → approved version stored with version hash → approved version only displayed to investors. Pitch changes: any material change requires re-approval. Risk warnings: FCA-mandated risk disclosure on every pitch page (\"Your capital is at risk. This type of investment is not suitable for most retail investors.\"). EIS/SEIS Integration: Enterprise Investment Scheme (EIS) and Seed Enterprise Investment Scheme (SEIS): companies with advance assurance from HMRC SEIS/EIS team are flagged. HMRC EIS compliance check API: verify advance assurance reference. SEIS/EIS certificate generation: after investment completion, SEIS3/EIS3 certificate generated for investor (enables 50%/30% income tax relief claim). Investor tax relief dashboard: tracks each investor's SEIS/EIS certificate status per investment. Companies House Due Diligence: Companies House API: company registration verification, director check (no disqualified directors), filing history review (accounts filed, confirmation statement current), SIC code (sector check — some sectors ineligible for SEIS/EIS), and PSC register (beneficial ownership). Automated due diligence report: generated at campaign approval — PDF attached to campaign record. Money laundering check: Experian commercial check + director KYC (Onfido).",
    "results": "Platform live at 18 weeks, £112,000 — under budget. Mobile conversion rate: 4% (legacy) → 31% (new platform). Appropriateness assessment failure rate: 34% (correctly filtering inappropriate retail investors). FCA financial promotion review: zero promotions rejected post-approval (legacy: 12 post-approval FCA queries in prior year). EIS/SEIS certificate generation: automated — previously 2 weeks manual. Campaigns funded: £8.4M in first 6 months on new platform.",
